s_post','',0),(775,2,'2015-02-24 12:03:34','2015-02-24 12:03:34','','/customer-insights','','publish','closed','closed','','775','','','2015-02-26 15:30:10','2015-02-26 15:30:10','',0,'',0,'leadpages_post','',0),(776,2,'2015-02-24 16:16:19','2015-02-24 16:16:19','','/user-analytics','','publish','closed','closed','','776','','','2015-02-24 16:16:26','2015-02-24 16:16:26','',0,'',0,'leadpages_post','',0),(777,2,'2015-02-24 16:17:45','2015-02-24 16:17:45','','/segmentation','','publish','closed','closed','','777','','','2015-02-24 16:17:45','2015-02-24 16:17:45','',0,'',0,'leadpages_post','',0),(779,2,'2015-02-24 16:19:43','2015-02-24 16:19:43','','/customer-profile','','publish','closed','closed','','779','','','2015-02-24 16:19:57','2015-02-24 16:19:57','',0,'',0,'leadpages_post','',0),(780,2,'2015-02-24 16:21:05','2015-02-24 16:21:05','','/customer-personas','','publish','closed','closed','','780','','','2015-02-24 16:21:05','2015-02-24 16:21:05','',0,'',0,'leadpages_post','',0),(781,2,'2015-02-24 16:23:48','2015-02-24 16:23:48','','/customer-intelligence','','publish','closed','closed','','781','','','2015-02-24 16:23:48','2015-02-24 16:23:48','',0,'',0,'leadpages_post','',0),(783,2,'2015-03-05 12:05:02','2015-03-05 12:05:02','<h3>Getting Started</h3>\r\nTo get started on Birdleaf all you need to do is upload a spreadsheet containing email addresses. Here is a step-by-step guide in creating an account and getting your first email addresses analyzed.\r\n\r\n<strong>Before You Start</strong>\r\n\r\nTo get started on Birdleaf you\'ll need to have a spreadsheet with some email addresses ready to upload to Birdleaf. We currently support the following formats:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Upload a .CSV file <img src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/csv_format.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"right\" /></li>\r\n	<li>Upload a .XLS file <img src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/xls_format.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"right\" /></li>\r\n	<li>Upload a .XLSX file <img src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/xlsx_format.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"right\" /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you have any other queries about the list format you can<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/troubleshooting-a-list-import\"> check out this article</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Creating An Account</strong>\r\n\r\nIt takes just a few minutes to set up an account with Birdleaf  Follow the steps below, and you’ll start getting key insights on your customers in no time.\r\n<span style=\"margin-left: 30px;\">\r\n<strong>1.</strong> Give your list a name. This can be deleted later.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Getting_Started_Step_1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1033\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Getting_Started_Step_1.jpg\" alt=\"Getting_Started_Step_1\" width=\"500\" height=\"264\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2.</strong> Add the file you want to analyze.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Getting_Started_Step_2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1032\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Getting_Started_Step_2.jpg\" alt=\"Getting_Started_Step_2\" width=\"500\" height=\"264\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>3.</strong> Choose a plan and enter your payment details.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Getting_Started_Step_3.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1031\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Getting_Started_Step_3.jpg\" alt=\"Getting_Started_Step_3\" width=\"500\" height=\"264\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</span>\r\nAnd thats it. You will then be directed to the application where you\'ll start getting insights on your customer base straight away. If you uploaded a big list it may take a bit of time to get through all the email addresses. We typically get through about 15000 emails an hour.\r\n\r\nIf you are need any help with setting up your account you can check out our <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/?cat=22\">FAQs</a>.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/?p=787\">Troubleshoot a List Import</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/?p=802\">Troubleshoot Analytics Dashboard</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/?p=804\">Troubleshoot Raw Data</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/?p=806\">Troubleshoot Subscriptions</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Getting Started with Birdleaf','','publish','closed','open','','getting-started-with-birdleaf','','','2015-08-10 15:36:53','2015-08-10 14:36:53','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=783',0,'post','',0),(787,2,'2015-03-05 12:04:05','2015-03-05 12:04:05','<h3 id=\"supporttitle\">How to import email addresses?</h3>\r\nYou can currently import email addresses to Birdleaf by uploading a spreadsheet containing the email addresses you wish to analyze.\r\n\r\nYou can add spreadsheets in the following formats to Birdleaf:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Upload a .CSV file <img src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/support_email_format_csv.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"right\" /></li>\r\n	<li>Upload a .XLS file <img src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/support_email_format_xls.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"right\" /></li>\r\n	<li>Upload a .XLSX file <img src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/support_email_format_xlsx.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"right\" /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p id=\"faqtitle\"><strong>Uploading a file</strong></p>\r\nWhen uploading a file to you need to ensure all column names are deleted to make sure there are no issues with the upload.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_support_add_emails_column.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-952\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_support_add_emails_column.jpg\" alt=\"birdleaf_support_add_emails_column\" width=\"500\" height=\"340\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p id=\"faqtitle\"><strong>Check the format.</strong></p>\r\nAs mentioned above, the only formats thatBirdleaf supports are CSV (.csv) or Excel (.xlsx, .xls). When saving your spreadsheet just double check that it\'s in one of these formats to avoid any issues. When a file is uploaded in the wrong format an error message will display.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/support_birdleaf_wrong_fomat.jpg\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-953 aligncenter\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/support_birdleaf_wrong_fomat.jpg\" alt=\"support_birdleaf_wrong_fomat\" width=\"500\" height=\"340\" /></a>\r\n<p id=\"faqtitle\"><strong>Uploaded a file and dashboard is empty?</strong></p>\r\nThis can sometimes happen if you uploaded a file in a correct format but haven\'t deleted the column names. If you\'ve tried to upload your list and have been unsuccessful try deleting all unnecessary columns and rows.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/support_addemails_columns_rows.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-955\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/support_addemails_columns_rows.jpg\" alt=\"support_addemails_columns_rows\" width=\"500\" height=\"340\" /></a></p>\r\nIf your emails are currently in <strong>column A</strong>  and you\'re dashboard is empty then you can let us know <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/support/\">here</a> and we\'ll get back to you straight away.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p id=\"faqtitle\"><b>How big a list can be uploaded?</b></p>\r\nIf you are having issues uploading a very large list consider breaking the list into smaller chunks of 50,000 subscribers for the upload. If that still doesn\'t work please <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/support/\">contact us directly</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p id=\"faqtitle\"><b>Can I add emails to my existing list?</b></p>\r\nYes. You can add email addresses to an existing list or to a new list. Just select which list you wish to add emails to from the drop down menu at the top of the screen and add the file you wish to upload.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p id=\"faqtitle\"><strong>Can I automatically add emails to birdleaf?</strong></p>\r\nCurrently the only way to upload email addresses is through the <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/add-emails\">Add Email</a> section in birdleaf. If you would like to have an integration to a email service you can let us know <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/support/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p id=\"faqtitle\"><strong>Can I view lists separately?</strong></p>\r\nYes. You can create as many different lists as you like. For help in creating multiple lists just <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/manage-multiple-lists-of-emails\">check out this article</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p id=\"faqtitle\"><strong>Can I delete a list of emails and upload a new list?</strong></p>\r\n\r\nTo delete a list from birdleaf all you have to do is select the dropdown menu from the top of the screen and hit the delete button beside the list mane. For all other queries about lists you can <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/manage-multiple-lists-of-emails\">check out this article</a>.','Troubleshoot a List Import','','publish','closed','open','','troubleshooting-a-list-import','','','2015-08-10 15:54:05','2015-08-10 14:54:05','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=787',0,'post','',0),(798,2,'2015-03-05 15:50:17','2015-03-05 15:50:17','','leaffy_leaf_leaf','','inherit','open','open','','leaffy_leaf_leaf','','','2015-03-05 15:50:17','2015-03-05 15:50:17','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/leaffy_leaf_leaf.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(802,2,'2015-03-05 12:03:17','2015-03-05 12:03:17','<strong>I uploaded a list and my dashboard is empty</strong>\r\n\r\nThis can happen because your list of emails didn\'t import correctly. You can troubleshoot a list import <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/?p=787\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What data can I see on the dashboard?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe dashboard provides you with an aggregate view of you of your customers demographical information. You can see Customer Personas, Location, Age, Gender, Job Function and Company Sector.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What are Customer Personas?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe customer persona section of the dashboard compares all the data from your customers email addresses to identify common trends and aggregates the data to show you your top three customer personas.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I filter through the data on the dashboard?</strong>\r\n\r\nCurrently the only way to filter through the data is through the <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/rawdata\">Raw Data</a> section of the application. If you are unsure how to filter through the raw data you can get help <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/?p=804\">here</a>.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to be able to filter through the data on the dashboard you can <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/support/\">contact us for early access</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Troubleshoot Analytics Dashboard','','publish','closed','open','','troubleshoot-analytics-dashboard','','','2015-06-10 17:28:33','2015-06-10 17:28:33','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=802',0,'post','',0),(804,2,'2015-03-05 12:02:11','2015-03-05 12:02:11','<strong>Can I export raw data?</strong>\r\n\r\nYes. You can currently filter through and export the raw data <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/raw-data\">here</a>. For tips on exporting the raw data just click <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/exporting-raw-data\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Why is there data missing for some email addresses?</strong>\r\n\r\nThis can happen because there is no publicly available information for that email address of the user. Often this happens when a user keeps all their information tied to their personal email address, but is using their work account for your product.\r\n\r\nIf you have any specific questions about the data provided feel free to <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/support/\">contact us here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I filter through the raw data?</strong>\r\n\r\nYes. To filter through the raw data you can input a parameter into the text box beneath the field you want to filter. For example, if you type CEO into the job field you will be returned with the emails of those people matching your criteria.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I email specific people directly from birdleaf?  </strong>\r\n\r\nUnfortunately we don\'t support this functionality. If there is an integration to a email marketing service you would like to have please <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/support/\">let us know</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Where does birdleaf get its data?</strong>\r\n\r\nWe combine information from hundreds of public websites, social networks, APIs and trusted partners.\r\n\r\nIf you have any specific questions about the data feel free to <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/support/\">contact us here</a>.','Troubleshoot Raw Data','','publish','closed','open','','troubleshoot-raw-data','','','2015-08-10 16:03:54','2015-08-10 15:03:54','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=804',0,'post','',0),(806,2,'2015-03-05 12:01:11','2015-03-05 12:01:11','<strong>How much does birdleaf cost?</strong>\r\n\r\nWe work on a volume based model so you only get charged for what you use. For more information on pricing just check out our pricing page<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/plans\"> here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Do I manually have to pay every month?</strong>\r\n\r\nNo. We automatically bill you each month and we\'ll notify you with your invoice.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Is the payment system secure?</strong>\r\n\r\nYes. We use <a href=\"https://stripe.com\">Stripe</a> to handle all our payments.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I upgrade my card details?</strong>\r\n\r\nYou can upgrade your card details by going to your <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/user/account\">Account</a> page and entering the new information.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>How can I cancel my subscription?</strong>\r\n\r\nYou can cancel your subscription by going to your <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/user/account\">Account</a> page and just click \"I\'m Sure\" at the bottom of the page.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I change my password?</strong>\r\n\r\nYes. You can upgrade your password in your <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/user/account\">Account</a> page.','Troubleshoot Subscriptions','','publish','closed','open','','troubleshoot-subscriptions','','','2015-08-10 16:05:34','2015-08-10 15:05:34','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=806',0,'post','',0),(811,2,'2015-03-05 21:26:50','2015-03-05 21:26:50','','BACKPAGE_1','','inherit','open','open','','backpage_1','','','2015-03-05 21:26:50','2015-03-05 21:26:50','',304,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/BACKPAGE_1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(812,2,'2015-03-05 21:28:21','2015-03-05 21:28:21','','HOME_BACK','','inherit','open','open','','home_back','','','2015-03-05 21:28:21','2015-03-05 21:28:21','',304,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/HOME_BACK.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(813,2,'2015-03-05 21:28:35','2015-03-05 21:28:35','','Screen Shot 2015-03-05 at 19.39.21','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-03-05-at-19-39-21','','','2015-03-05 21:28:35','2015-03-05 21:28:35','',304,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/Screen-Shot-2015-03-05-at-19.39.21.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(814,2,'2015-03-05 21:40:47','2015-03-05 21:40:47','','backfill','','inherit','open','open','','backfill','','','2015-03-05 21:40:47','2015-03-05 21:40:47','',304,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/backfill.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(815,2,'2015-03-05 21:43:48','2015-03-05 21:43:48','','111','','inherit',