(847,2,'2015-03-12 14:05:29','2015-03-12 14:05:29','','birdleaf_footer_logoicon','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_footer_logoicon','','','2015-03-12 14:05:29','2015-03-12 14:05:29','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/birdleaf_footer_logoicon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(848,2,'2015-03-12 14:30:57','2015-03-12 14:30:57','','birdleaf_birdleaf','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_birdleaf','','','2015-03-12 14:30:57','2015-03-12 14:30:57','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/birdleaf_birdleaf.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(850,2,'2015-03-12 16:25:33','2015-03-12 16:25:33','','ImageADMC','','inherit','open','open','','imageadmc','','','2015-03-12 16:25:33','2015-03-12 16:25:33','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ImageADMC.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(852,2,'2015-03-12 17:11:42','2015-03-12 17:11:42','','birdleafmainimage','','inherit','open','open','','birdleafmainimage','','','2015-03-12 17:11:42','2015-03-12 17:11:42','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/birdleafmainimage.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(858,2,'2015-03-05 12:00:40','2015-03-05 12:00:40',' You can currently filter through and export the raw data <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/raw-data\">here</a>. You currently have 3 options when exporting the raw data. Firstly you can export all the raw data we\'ve collected on your customers.  Alternatively you can just export the data visible in your table incase you\'ve been filtering it based on parameters such as Full Name and Age. Finally you have the option to export the specific data points you want by unchecking the options you don\'t want to export.\r\n\r\nJust follow the steps below to export your raw data:\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 50px;\">1. Select the <strong>drop down menu</strong> from the top right hand corner of the table.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 50px;\">2. Filter though the raw data you want to export. You can either export all the raw data or export based on parameters such as Full Name and Age.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 150px;\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Raw-data-export.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-859\" style=\"border-color: #69d291;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Raw-data-export.jpg\" alt=\"Raw-data-export\" width=\"240\" height=\"350\" border=\"1\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 50px;\"> 3. The raw data will download once you select and option.</p>\r\n<strong>Safari Users</strong>\r\n\r\nCurrently if you are using Safari there is one extra step you will have to take when exporting the data. Follow the steps as outlined above. When you select <strong>Export all data </strong>or <strong>Export visible data</strong> you will be redirected to a new tab with all the raw data scattered across the page. To download it you\'ll need to right click on the page and select <strong>Save Page As...</strong> from the drop down menu. You will then be presented with a pop up with one of the options being <strong>Format</strong>.  From this drop down menu you\'ll need to select <strong>Page Source</strong> and click <strong>Save</strong>. The final thing you\'ll need to do is change to the file extension from <strong>.</strong><strong>txt</strong> to <strong>.csv</strong>. To do this you need to rename the file and simply change the text <strong>.txt</strong> at the end of the name to <strong>.csv</strong> and you\'ll be able to access your raw data.\r\n\r\nIf you experience any issues please <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/support\"><span style=\"color: red;\">let us know</span></a>.','Exporting Raw Data','','publish','closed','open','','exporting-raw-data','','','2015-06-10 17:23:18','2015-06-10 17:23:18','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=858',0,'post','',0),(859,2,'2015-03-18 10:54:11','2015-03-18 10:54:11','','Raw-data-export','','inherit','open','open','','raw-data-export','','','2015-03-18 10:54:11','2015-03-18 10:54:11','',858,'