notify the other party of such cessation.\r\n\r\n10.3 If the event of Force Majeure shall continue for more than 45 days then either party shall have the right to terminate this Agreement on written notice to the other party.\r\n\r\n<strong>11. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY INDEMNITY</strong>\r\n\r\n11.1 The Service Provider shall indemnify the Customer from and against all damages, costs, charges and expenses arising from or incurred by reason of any infringement or alleged infringement of any third party intellectual property rights in consequence of the authorised use or possession of any deliverables provided by the Service Provider to the Customer, subject to the following:\r\n\r\n(a) The Customer shall promptly notify the Service Provider in writing of any alleged infringement of which it has notice;\r\n\r\n(b) The Customer must make no admissions without the Service Provider’s prior written consent; and\r\n\r\n(c) The Customer, at the Service Provider’s request and expense, shall allow the Service Provider to conduct any negotiations or litigation and/or settle any claim. The Customer shall give the Service Provider all reasonable assistance. The costs incurred or recovered in such negotiations or settled claim shall be for the Service Provider’s account.\r\n\r\n<strong>12. VARIATIONS</strong>\r\n\r\n12.1 If the Customer wishes to make a variation to the Services, then the Customer shall promptly arrange a meeting with the Service Provider to discuss such variation.\r\n\r\n12.2 The Service Provider shall then submit to the Customer as soon as reasonably practicable a quotation for such variations, additions or modifications specifying the changes (if any) which will be required to the charges set out in Clause 2 and the adjustments which will be required to the description of the Services in Schedule 1.\r\n\r\n12.3  Within fourteen days of such quotation, the Customer may elect by notice to the Service Provider either:\r\n\r\n(a) to accept such quotation in which case this Agreement shall be amended accordingly; or\r\n\r\n(b) to withdraw the proposed variations in which case this Agreement shall continue in force unchanged.\r\n\r\n<strong>13. Waiver</strong>\r\n\r\nNo delay, neglect, or forbearance on the part of either party in enforcing against the other party any term or condition of this Agreement shall either be or be deemed to be a waiver or in any way prejudice any right of that party under this Agreement.\r\n\r\n<strong>14. NO PARTNERSHIP, AGENCY ETC</strong>\r\n\r\nNothing in this Agreement shall create, or be deemed to create, a partnership or the relationship of principal and agent or employer and employee between the parties.\r\n\r\n<strong>15. ENTIRE AGREEMENT</strong>\r\n\r\nThis Agreement contains the entire agreement between the parties with respect to its subject matter, supersedes all previous agreements and understandings between the parties with respect to its subject matter, and may not be modified except by an instrument in writing signed by the duly authorised representatives of the parties.\r\n\r\n<strong>16. ASSIGNMENT AND SUB-CONTRACTING</strong>\r\n\r\n16.1 Neither party shall be entitled to assign any of its rights and/or obligations under this Agreement without the prior written consent of the other party.\r\n\r\n<strong>17. SEVERABILITY</strong>\r\n\r\nIn the event that any provision of this Agreement shall be determined to be partially void or unenforceable by any court or body of competent jurisdiction or by virtue of any legislation to which it is subject or by virtue of any other reason whatsoever, it shall be void or unenforceable to that extent only and no further and the validity and enforceability of any of the other provisions of this Agreement shall not be affected.\r\n\r\n<strong>18. GENERAL</strong>\r\n\r\n18.1 In this Agreement, and the Schedules hereto, the masculine gender shall include the feminine and neuter and the singular number shall include the plural and vice versa and words importing persons shall include firms or companies.\r\n\r\n18.2 Unless otherwise provided in this Agreement any reference to a section, clause, paragraph or sub-paragraph shall be a reference to a section, clause, paragraph or sub-paragraph (as the case may be) of this Agreement and any reference in a clause or paragraph shall be a reference to the clause or paragraph in which the reference is contained unless it appears from the context that a reference to some other provision is intended.\r\n\r\n18.3 The section headings and captions to the clauses in this Agreement are inserted for convenience of reference only and shall not be considered a part of or affect the construction or interpretation of this Agreement.\r\n\r\n<strong>19. MARKETING</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Customer gives the Service Provider a perpetual world-wide license to use the Customer\'s company assets and logos, unless the Service Provider agrees in writing otherwise. These assets and logos will be used purely for marketing and sales efforts, such as being displayed on the home page.\r\n\r\n<strong>20. GOVERNING LAW</strong>\r\n\r\nThis Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of Ireland and the each of the parties submits to the jurisdiction of the Irish Courts for the resolution of disputes hereunder.\r\n\r\n<strong>21. DATA RESTRICTIONS</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Customer will not, and will require any and all third parties to which it provides any data from the Service Provider (“Data Recipients”) to not, use such data for the purposes of cookie tracking, ad exchanges, ad networks, data brokerages, sending electronic communications (including email) in violation of applicable law, or any other activity or purpose identified as prohibited by Birdleaf in any communication sent to the Customer. If Birdleaf informs the Customer that a specified activity or purpose is prohibited, the Customer will ensure that any and all Data Recipients immediately cease processing of any such data for the prohibited activity or purpose. If the Customer is not subject to the laws based on the EU Data Protection Directive 95/46 or Swiss Federal Data Protection law, the Customer hereby agrees to either (i) subscribe to the Safe Harbor principles or (ii) contractually agree to provide at least the same level of protection for Personal Data as is required by the relevant Safe Harbor principles.','Terms of Service','','publish','open','open','','terms-of-service','','','2015-09-07 17:57:13','2015-09-07 16:57:13','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?page_id=866',0,'page','',0),(870,2,'2015-04-15 13:32:39','2015-04-15 13:32:39','<strong>1. Do I need to disclose personal data to Birdleaf for the purposes of the services?</strong>\r\n\r\nYes, the services involve gathering customer insights from their email address. In connection with those services, we ask you to provide us with email addresses. However, our template contract imposes data protection and confidentiality obligations on us in respect of such data, which will be of comfort to you. For further details, see below.\r\n\r\n<strong>2. Is my disclosure of data to you compliant with the Data Protection Acts?</strong>\r\n\r\nProvided that you are entitled to have the data in your possession, then there is no difficulty with disclosing the data to us. This is because we are only processing this data as a data processor on your behalf. We are subject to the Irish Data Protection Acts, 1988 and 2003 as a data processor (an entity which processes data on your behalf).\r\n\r\n<strong>3. I have heard that there are certain contractual provisions which need to be included in contracts in respect of data protection. What are they?</strong>\r\n\r\nUnder Section 2C(3) of the Data Protection Acts, where a data processor (i.e. Birdleaf)processes personal data on behalf of a data controller (i.e., you, the customer), then the data controller is obliged to ensure that there is a written contract in place with the data processor which includes certain specified language. Although that is your obligation, we have facilitate this by including the necessary language (and significant obligations on ourselves) in our standard contract, see section 9. This obliges us:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To process personal data in accordance with your instructions;</li>\r\n	<li>To have in place proper data security measures; and</li>\r\n	<li>to notify you of any data security incidents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>4. When I disclose personal data to you, could it be hosted/stored outside Europe?</strong>\r\n\r\nSuch personal data may be stored outside Europe if, and only if, it is relevant and necessary for the performance of the services (see clause 9.2). We are happy to discuss with you the way in which this can be achieved in compliance with the Data Protection Acts, e.g:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>where you have obtained the consent of the persons to whom the data relate; or</li>\r\n	<li>where we enter into data transfer agreements in the form approved by the European Commission; or</li>\r\n	<li>for transfers to the United States, where the transferee is subject to the US Safe Harbour Principles.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>5. Are you obliged to register with the Data Protection Commissioner?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe 2007 Registration Regulations oblige certain categories of data controllers to register. We do not fall within any of those categories.\r\n\r\nThe 2007 Registration Regulations only oblige data processors to register where they process personal data on behalf of registered data controllers, e.g. banks, insurance companies etc. We do not process on behalf of such entities, and are therefore not registered.\r\n\r\n<strong>6. You have provided me with your standard draft agreement. Should you not sign a bespoke agreement which I provide to you?</strong>\r\n\r\nIt is, of course, an option to ask us to negotiate and sign a different agreement. However, our standard agreement should give you the comfort which you need. Our contract is designed to be fair and to include reasonable obligations on both parties. For example:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We commit to providing you with the services outlined in a schedule;</li>\r\n	<li>You commit to the payments outlined in the schedule;</li>\r\n	<li>We commit to provide services with due skill, care and diligence. We set this out as an express warranty;</li>\r\n	<li>We grant you a wide licence to use any deliverables/work product which we develop as part of the services;</li>\r\n	<li>We indemnify you where our work product transpires to infringe third party intellectual property rights;</li>\r\n	<li>We agree to standard, reciprocal confidentiality obligations;</li>\r\n	<li>We are subject to robust data protection obligations; and</li>\r\n	<li>Our contract gives us the flexibility to agree to amended and additional services if you wish to avail of these.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>7. How long am I committed to the contract?</strong>\r\n\r\nA month to month contract which may be terminated at any time on one month’s notice.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','FAQ','','publish','open','open','','faq','','','2015-04-15 13:32:39','2015-04-15 13:32:39','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?page_id=870',0,'page','',0),(872,2,'2015-04-23 17:16:33','2015-04-23 17:16:33','Are you one of those people who used Rapportive to find email addresses or information about the people you\'re talking to? The <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://rapportive.com/\">Rapportive</a> of old is very much dead and buried and while it still exists and you can still use it, all of thefunctionality that drew users to it in the first place is now unfortunately gone. Fortunately for all its fans a lot of good alternatives have popped up since LinkedIn neutered the once awesome tool.\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>FullContact</strong></h3>\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://www.fullcontact.com/gmail/\">FullContact</a> is an awesome replacement for Rapportive! Similar to Rapportive, users are able to type in or hover over a new email address in order to see detailed contact information in the sidebar of your inbox, including things like their name, location, Job Title, Company , recent tweets, and links to their social networks. It even goes a step further than the Rapportive of old by displaying rich company information. You\'ll be able to see things like the company\'s founding date, company size, phone number, address and more.\r\n\r\nFullContact also allows you to make notes and tag people. The only caveat with this feature is after 5,000 contacts , you\'ll have to upgrade to a premium account, but I\'m guessing that having 5,000 contacts is a good problem to have so shelling out the $9.99 per month won\'t be too big an issue.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-879 aligncenter\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Rapportive_Alternatives_FullContact.jpg\" alt=\"Rapportive Alternative FullContact\" width=\"480\" height=\"456\" />\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://www.fullcontact.com/gmail/\" target=\"_blank\">FullContact</a>(Free) | Availability <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/fullcontact-for-gmail/cnaibnehbbinoohhjafknihmlopdhhip?hl=en-US\" target=\"_blank\">Google Chrome</a> &amp; <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://www.fullcontact.com/iphone/\" target=\"_blank\">iOS</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Vibe</strong></h3>\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://vibeapp.co/\" target=\"_blank\">VibeApp</a> is also a very slick-looking alternative to Rapportive and it pulls in a lot of data. Like the rest of the competitors Rapportive throne VibeApp pulls up detailed contact information, links to their social profiles, organizations they\'ve worked for, and associated websites in the sidebar of your inbox. It also pulls out topics or keywords that best describes the person but having tested it with a few email addresses its a bit hit and miss.\r\n\r\nThere are a few key differentiators between VibeApp and those trying to replace Rapportive. Firstly, it isn\'t restricted to your inbox, it will work across your browser anywhere that an email address is displayed. For example, if you see someone\'s email address on LinkedIn all you have to do is hover your mouse over it and it will show you all the other social accounts associated with that email address. Secondly, it\'s not limited to a single email address in a message.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-880\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Rapportive_Alternatives_Vibe.jpg\" alt=\"Rapportive Alternative Vibe\" width=\"480\" height=\"456\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://vibeapp.co/\" target=\"_blank\">Vibe</a>(Free) | Availability <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/vibe-for-google-chrome/dbnookjgoaaelhciadikaadnkgmiamei\" target=\"_blank\">Google Chrome</a>, <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/vibe-for-firefox/\" target=\"_blank\">Firefox</a>, <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewSoftware?id=887337013&amp;mt=12\" target=\"_blank\">Mac</a> &amp; <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewSoftware?id=883587113&amp;mt=8\" target=\"_blank\">iOS</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Sidekick</strong></h3>\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://www.getsidekick.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sidekick</a> by Hubspot is a very need alternative to Rapportive giving you a wealth of contact insight in your inbox. It has all the functionality of Rapportive and a lot, lot more! In the sidebar of your inbox you\'ll see your contacts social profiles,  all their recent tweets, location, and their professional history. Now for the more part. Sidekick will show you your email history with that contact. It tracks and analyzes the behaviors of the person that receives your email so you can see exactly what they did with it.\r\n\r\nNow for the more part! Sidekick will also show you your email history with that contact. It tracks and analyzes the behaviors of the person that receives your email so you can see exactly what they did with it. How many times your email has been opened, if they clicked on the link in the email, what device they read your email on. Really useful insights so you can determine  the effectiveness of your email strategy. For example, if a potential client is reading your emails on their phone, you will want to tailor your content to be as short and concise as possible whereas if they\'re on their laptop you may want to go into a bit more depth.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-881\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Rapportive_Alternatives_Sidekick.jpg\" alt=\"Rapportive Alternative Sidekick by Hubspot\" width=\"480\" height=\"456\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://www.getsidekick.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sidekick</a> (Free) | Availability <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/sidekick-by-hubspot/oiiaigjnkhngdbnoookogelabohpglmd\">Google Chrome</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Discover.ly</strong></h3>\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://discover.ly/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Discoverly</strong></a> also sheds light on your email contacts regardless if you have been in contact with them before. It shows you all relevant info and social connections about email contacts. It\'s similar to VibeApp in that you can view more data about your connections when viewing profiles across the web. For example, you can see your mutual Facebook friends on LinkedIn, or see Facebook and LinkedIn info on Twitter.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-882\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Rapportive_Alternatives_Discoverly.jpg\" alt=\"Rapportive Alternative Discoverly\" width=\"480\" height=\"456\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://discover.ly/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Discoverly</strong></a>(Free) | Availability <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/discoverly/dijhcpbkalfgkcebgoncjmfpbamihgaf?hl=en-US\">Google Chrome</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"> <strong>Bottom Line</strong></h3>\r\nWhen it comes to the best alternative to Rapportive I would have to go with <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://www.fullcontact.com/gmail/\">FullContact</a>. This is due to the quality of data you get back and it is also useful to make notes on each contact. That said the data quality ofHubspots <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://www.getsidekick.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sidekick</a> is just as good as it appears it is powered by <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://www.fullcontact.com/gmail/\">FullContact</a> and it adds on a ton of features like tracking your email history with a contact which is really handy. It does seem that the search for a good replacement to Rapportive is now over with there being a lot of good options out there now.\r\n\r\nIf I failed to mention or if you have any feedback on the above feel free to comment below.','Rapportive Alternatives That Don\'t Suck','','publish','open','open','','rapportive-alternatives-that-dont-suck','','','2015-04-24 16:44:39','2015-04-24 16:44:39','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=872',0,'post','',0),(873,2,'2015-04-21 17:52:39','2015-04-21 17:52:39','','Login','','publish','open','open','','sign-in','','','2015-05-07 17:04:17','2015-05-07 17:04:17','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=873',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(879,2,'2015-04-23 15:06:30','2015-04-23 15:06:30','Rapportive Alternative FullContact','Rapportive_Alternatives_FullContact','Rapportive Alternative FullContact','inherit','open','open','','rapportive_alternatives_fullcontact','','','2015-04-23 15:08:21','2015-04-23 15:08:21','',872,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Rapportive_Alternatives_FullContact.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(880,2,'2015-04-23 15:10:19','2015-04-23 15:10:19','Rapportive Alternative Vibe','Rapportive_Alternatives_Vibe','','inherit','open','open','','rapportive_alternatives_vibe','','','2015-04-23 15:10:36','2015-04-23 15:10:36','',872,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Rapportive_Alternatives_Vibe.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(881,2,'2015-04-23 15:10:59','2015-04-23 15:10:59','Rapportive Alternative Sidekick by Hubspot','Rapportive_Alternatives_Sidekick','','inherit','open','open','','rapportive_alternatives_sidekick','','','2015-04-23 15:11:19','2015-04-23 15:11:19','',872,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Rapportive_Alternatives_Sidekick.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(882,2,'2015-04-23 15:13:51','2015-04-23 15:13:51','Rapportive Alternative Discoverly','Rapportive_Alternatives_Discoverly','','inherit','open','open','','rapportive_alternatives_discoverly','','','2015-04-23 15:14:10','2015-04-23 15:14:10','',872,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Rapportive_Alternatives_Discoverly.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(884,2,'2015-04-23 19:39:53','2015-04-23 19:39:53','Google Drive is close to the top of the list when it comes to what application I use most during the day. It\'s a really useful tool for marketers, from taking notes at conferences to creating surveys for blog content and being able to access all your documents across multiple devices.\r\n\r\nGoogle Drive has really upped its game of late. You get up to 15GB for free, 100GB for $2 a month, or 1TB for $9.99 a month. Hard to complain with that. While Google Drive is easy to use you may not be aware that there are several easy(free) ways to get even more out of the service.  You can use Drive save space on your hard drive, recover old version of a file, save content straight from a website and much, much more.\r\n\r\nCheck out the list of Google Drive tricks to make your work even more productive.\r\n<h3><strong>1) Use Drive to attach larger files to emails</strong></h3>\r\nGoogle Drive has made sending files and photos as email attachments sexy again, apparently. When you’re attaching files from you computer, you can only attach files up to 25 MB. But, by inserting files using Drive, you can now send a file up to 10 GB. The recipients can easily view them online. And if the files aren\'t shared, Google Drive will prompt you to do that before the email is sent.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-8441 size-full\" style=\"border: 1px solid #86c177;\" title=\"Google Drive Tricks_Attachment\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Drive_Attachment.png\" alt=\"Google Drive Tricks_Attachment\" width=\"335\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\nAlso unlike traditional attachments where you have to wait for the file to upload, attaching a file through Drive doesn’t require you to re-upload the file. Simps.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>2) File Versions</strong></h3>\r\nIf you collaborate on documents with colleagues or clients it helps to see exactly what changes were made and who made them. Did you know you can use Google Drive for this? Drive keeps 30 days worth of file revisions (up to 100 versions).\r\n\r\nTo view older versions of the file, just head to the Google Drive website:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">1. Navigate to the file you want to see the revision history of.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">2. Right click on the file and click <strong>Manage revisions…</strong> from the drop down menu.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-8461 size-full\" style=\"border: 1px solid #86c177;\" title=\"Google Drive Tricks_Version Control\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Version-Control.png\" alt=\"Google Drive Tricks_Version Control\" width=\"333\" height=\"373\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">3. Now you can see all the versions of the file as it was updated.</p>\r\nUnlike Dropbox, if you rename the file or change the file location you can still see the history of the file.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>3) Make Google Drive your default documents folder</strong></h3>\r\nYou might want to make Google Drive as the default documents folder considering the features it offers.\r\n\r\nFor Mac users, Open Terminal (in Utilities) and type <strong>cd Google\\ Drive/</strong>. Hit enter, and then type <strong>In –s~/documents /documents</strong>. Hit enter again and watch the magic happen.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-8561\" style=\"border: 1px solid #86c177;\" title=\"Google Drive Tricks_Terminal OSX\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Drive_Terminal-OSX.png\" alt=\"Google Drive Tricks_Terminal OSX\" width=\"579\" height=\"101\" /></p>\r\nFor windows users, right-click on your <strong>Documents </strong>folder, click <strong>Properties</strong>, click <strong>Include a folder</strong>, choose your Google Drive folder and finally select it and click <strong>Set save location</strong>. And that’s it, next time you save a document in a program like Microsoft Word; Google Drive will be selected as the default save location.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>4) Work Offline </strong></h3>\r\nMake files available offline so you can view them when your phone or tablet loses service, like on a plane or in a building with a bad connection.\r\n\r\nTo make files available offline just head to the Google Drive app on your phone or tablet:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">1. Navigate to the file you want to be available offline.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">2. Click on the <strong>Info icon</strong> to the right of the file name.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-8661\" style=\"border: 1px solid #86c177;\" title=\"Google Drive Tricks_Offline\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Drive_Offline1.png\" alt=\"Google Drive Tricks_Offline\" width=\"381\" height=\"430\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">3. Slide the <strong>Available Offline </strong>toggle to On.</p>\r\nNow that file will be saved to your mobile device so you can view and edit it when you’re offline.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>5) Restore file from bin</strong></h3>\r\nAccidentally deleted a file from Google Drive on the desktop? No biggie, just head to the Google Drive website and log in to its online version, click <strong>Bin</strong> on the left menu. And there you go, all the files you’ve deleted.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-8621\" style=\"border: 1px solid #86c177;\" title=\"Google Drive Tricks_Recover from Bin\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Recover-from-Bin.png\" alt=\"Google Drive Tricks_Recover from Bin\" width=\"418\" height=\"195\" /></p>\r\nNow all you have to do is check the box beside the file you want to recover and just click <strong>Restore</strong>. Emergency over!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>6) Use Forms to Collect Data</strong></h3>\r\nGoogle Forms lets you run a survey or quickly create a team roster with a simple online form. Whatever information has been input into the form will be automatically compiled into a spreadsheet, neatly organised so you can analyse the results.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-8641\" style=\"border: 1px solid #86c177;\" title=\"Google Dirve Tricks_Google Form\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Google-Form.png\" alt=\"Google Dirve Tricks_Google Form\" width=\"337\" height=\"265\" /></p>\r\nTo create a Form just head to the Google Drive website, click on the <strong>Create</strong> option and select <strong>Form. </strong>From here you’ll be able to set up the form.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>7) Use stars to flag key files</strong></h3>\r\nStars allow you to identify important files for quick access. To \"star\" a file, just head to the Google Drive website or the mobile app and click on the star on the left hand side of the file name.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-8711\" style=\"border: 1px solid #86c177;\" title=\"Google Drive Tricks_Star File\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Drive_Star-File.png\" alt=\"Google Drive Tricks_Star File\" width=\"361\" height=\"141\" /></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>8) Annotation App</strong></h3>\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://www.gingerlabs.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Notability</strong></a> is really responsive note taking and annotating app that ensures there\'s no more A4 pads or sticky notes cluttering up your office. You can import files from Google Drive and add your own notes to the document. So if you\'re asked to review a new sales contract, you can import the document from Google Drive, add your notes, and upload it back to Drive so everyone can see your feedback. You can also automatically back up the notes to Google Drive as PDFs.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-15089\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Dropbox_productivity_apps_notability.jpg\" alt=\"Dropbox_productivity_apps\" width=\"295\" height=\"368\" />\r\n\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://www.gingerlabs.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Notability</a> ($4.99) | Availability <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/ie/app/notability/id360593530?mt=8\" target=\"_blank\">iOS</a>\r\n<h3><strong>9) Document Editor</strong></h3>\r\nThis one is a bit less straight forward as Google have split up the Drive editing suite, meaning you now require standalone apps to edit documents. For the Google format files you’ll need to download <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://www.google.ie/docs/about/\" target=\"_blank\">Docs</a>, <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://www.google.ie/sheets/about/\" target=\"_blank\">Sheets</a>, and <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://www.google.ie/slides/about/\" target=\"_blank\">Slides</a> apps. For Microsoft Office format files - Word, Powerpoint, and Excel - you can use Quickoffice. However, Google have recently announced they are going to push an update to beef up the Drive editing apps to allow you edit MS Office files, but it hasn’t been released yet.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Google_Drive_Productivity_Apps_Quickoffice.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-15149\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Google_Drive_Productivity_Apps_Quickoffice.jpg\" alt=\"Google_Drive_Productivity_Apps_Quickoffice\" width=\"295\" height=\"369\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"http://www.google.ie/docs/about/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">Drive Editing Apps</a> (Free) | Availability <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/google-docs/id842842640?mt=8\" target=\"_blank\">iOS</a> &amp; <a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.google.android.apps.docs.editors.docs&amp;hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">Android</a>\r\n<h3><strong>10) Save to Google Drive</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As you might guess from the name, this extension lets you save <span style=\"color: #444444;\">content from anywhere on the web and store it neatly in Drive. Once the extension is installed, anytime you see a link or an image you want, you simply right click on the content and select the \"Save to Google Drive\" option. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-15121\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Chrome-Extensions-For-Google-Drive_Save-to-Drive.jpg\" alt=\"Chrome-Extensions-For-Google-Drive_Save-to-Drive\" width=\"550\" height=\"337\" /></p>\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/save-to-google-drive/gmbmikajjgmnabiglmofipeabaddhgne/details\" target=\"_blank\">Save to Google Drive</a> (Free)\r\n<h4><strong>11) Black Menu</strong></h4>\r\nThis extension is an in-browser pop-up so to speak, that gives you access to all Google services - probably making your overall Google experience better, not just Drive. The Drive page allows you to easily upload a file directly in Black Menu for Google, or create a new document via the create menu. It also provides a search bar so you can search your entire Drive account without having to leave the web page you\'re on.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-15116\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Chrome-Extensions-For-Google-Drive_Black-Menu.jpg\" alt=\"Chrome-Extensions-For-Google-Drive_Black-Menu\" width=\"550\" height=\"337\" />\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/black-menu-for-google/eignhdfgaldabilaaegmdfbajngjmoke\" target=\"_blank\">Black Menu</a> (Free)\r\n<h4><strong>12) Save text to Google Drive</strong></h4>\r\nSimilarly to \'Save to Google Drive\', this extension lets you save content from the web to Google Drive. Except instead of images and links, you can save web text content. If you see an article you want to save, all you do is hit the \"Save Text to Google Drive\" extension and all the text in the article will be saved to a new document in Drive.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-15120\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Chrome-Extensions-For-Google-Drive_Save-Text-to-Google-Drive.jpg\" alt=\"Chrome-Extensions-For-Google-Drive_Save-Text-to-Google-Drive\" width=\"550\" height=\"337\" />\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/save-text-to-google-drive/gkcckpoladnboalokmkldjabamjpkafo\" target=\"_blank\">Save Text to Google Drive</a> (Free)\r\n<h3><strong>13) Drive Notepad</strong></h3>\r\nYou can view and edit all kinds of text documents in your browser with this extension. It includes syntax highlighting for majority of scripting and programming languages.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-15117\" src=\"http://clouddock.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Chrome-Extensions-For-Google-Drive_Drive-NotePad.jpg\" alt=\"Chrome-Extensions-For-Google-Drive_Drive-NotePad\" width=\"550\" height=\"337\" />\r\n\r\n<a style=\"color: #86c177;\" href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/drive-notepad/gpgjomejfimnbmobcocilppikhncegaj\" target=\"_blank\">Drive Notepad</a> (Free)\r\n\r\nThese Google Drive tricks are really easy to start using and it is a sure way to make your day even more productive. If I missed and google drive tricks or if you have any feedback be sure to leave a comment below. Thanks for reading!','13 Google Drive Tricks You Didn\'t Know About','','publish','open','open','','13-google-drive-tricks-you-didnt-know-about','','','2015-04-24 16:56:14','2015-04-24 16:56:14','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=884',0,'post','',0),(885,2,'2015-04-24 11:22:29','2015-04-24 11:22:29','','BGa','','inherit','open','open','','bga','','','2015-04-24 11:22:29','2015-04-24 11:22:29','',304,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/BGa.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(886,2,'2015-04-24 11:39:08','2015-04-24 11:39:08','','Birdleaf Online Logo','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf-online-logo','','','2015-04-24 11:39:08','2015-04-24 11:39:08','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Birdleaf-Online-Logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(887,2,'2015-04-24 11:40:32','2015-04-24 11:40:32','','Birdleaf Homepage Logo','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf-homepage-logo','','','2015-04-24 11:40:32','2015-04-24 11:40:32','',0,'http://birdleaf.