sh','open','open','','some-quick-housekeeping','','','2015-06-15 18:12:46','2015-06-15 17:12:46','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?page_id=971',0,'page','',0),(973,2,'2015-06-15 18:10:26','2015-06-15 17:10:26','','dvlLVHF','','inherit','open','open','','dvllvhf','','','2015-06-15 18:10:26','2015-06-15 17:10:26','',971,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/dvlLVHF.gif',0,'attachment','image/gif',0),(977,3,'2015-08-16 14:36:28','2015-08-16 13:36:28','<div style=\"max-width: 730px; margin: 0 auto;\">\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to your marketing efforts and deciding on what channels you should focus on it is really important to have a clear picture of your customer personas. These are fictional, generalized representations of your ‘ideal customers’ designed to help you understand your customers and potential customers better.\r\n\r\nThese cluster of customers should exhibit similar behavioural patterns in their purchasing decisions, use of technology or products, customer service preferences, lifestyle choices, and the like. Therefore how you market to each persona can change drastically depending on the customer segment makeup.\r\n<blockquote style=\"margin-left: 25px;\">Customer<a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/33491/Everything-Marketers-Need-to-Research-Create-Detailed-Buyer-Personas-Template.aspx\"> </a>personas are a semi-fictional representation of your ideal customer based on market research and real data about your existing customers.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/buyer-persona-definition-under-100-sr\" target=\"_blank\">Hubspot</a></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h3><b>The basic customer persona template</b></h3>\r\nCreating your customer personas is quite straightforward, as regardless of your business there are a few common elements that should be included for a customer persona to be as effective as possible.\r\n\r\nA lot of these templates include the same basic information like <strong>who</strong> the person is, <strong>what</strong> problems they have, and <strong>how</strong> to acquire these customers. Here is a quick overview on what you should include in your customer persona template:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"  wp-image-978 aligncenter\" style=\"max-width: 85%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_template_blank.jpg\" alt=\"customer persona template\" />\r\n<h4><strong>Who?</strong></h4>\r\nHere you\'re summing up common personal and professional demographics. These data points can be very useful when advertising as on a lot of ad networks you can set a lot of demographical filters to target people that match this demographical criteria.\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 75px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Basic demographics</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Age</li>\r\n	<li>Gender</li>\r\n	<li>Location</li>\r\n	<li>Family</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Professional demographics</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Job Title</li>\r\n	<li>Industry</li>\r\n	<li>Company Size</li>\r\n	<li>Company Revenue</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>What?</strong></h4>\r\nUnderstanding this part is key in empathizing with the customer. This relates to more specific traits like their personality, values, interests, and lifestyles. The basic demographics provide you with the ‘who’, whereas the Psychographics provide you with the ‘what’.\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 75px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Problems</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What problems does the customer have that you can solve?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Goals</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What is their main goal motivating them to look for a solution?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Values</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What\'s the customers expectations of your product?</li>\r\n	<li>What are their objections during the buying process?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><b>Why?</b></h4>\r\nThis section of the customer persona is all about your marketing message and how you will acquire new customers that fit the specific customer persona. For each customer persona you have how you explain your product should change along with the route to these customers.\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 75px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Product Benefit</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What benefit does your product offer the customer?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Marketing</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>How will you describe your product?</li>\r\n	<li>What routes will you use to reach these customers?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nTo be successful at creating customer personas you need to accurately define who the person is, what their problems and goals are, and how you will explain your marketing message.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"max-width: 730px; margin: 0 auto;\">\r\n<h3><b>Sample Customer Persona</b></h3>\r\nNow that we have the template to start developing our customer personas here is a sample one. This sample customer persona is for a software company that supplies recruitment software that matches potential candidates to available job roles. They sell to customers across a wide range of industries and company sizes. This is one of their personas for a medium sized technology company.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"  wp-image-978 aligncenter\" style=\"max-width: 85%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_template_example.jpg\" alt=\"customer persona template\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"max-width: 730px; margin: 0 auto;\">\r\n<h3><b>Why You Should Have Customer Personas</b></h3>\r\nAt a high level, developing strong customer personas will result in more efficient and more cost effective marketing. They allow you to clearly segment your target audience into different groups meaning you can personalize and tailor your marketing for your different segments. For example, by segmenting your customer base into three groups you can send tailored content to each group meaning the content is more relevant and actionable for the end user leading to a better customer experience.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>SEE ALSO: <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/how-to-create-a-customer-persona\">How to create a customer persona</a></strong></p>\r\nIt also allows you, the marketer, to build a stronger brand by conveying stronger more relevant messaging and increase your return on investment on your marketing spend by focusing on the channels that will work in acquiring new ‘ideal customers’.\r\n\r\nThe easiest and most accurate source of information for your customer personas should be your existing customer base. Based on your current customers and what you know about them see if you can fill in data points needed for a rich customer persona. If you can’t fill out everything then the quickest way to fill in the gaps is by surveying or interviewing a random selection of your customers.\r\n\r\nWhen creating your customer personas I suggest starting out with a small amount, like 3 or 4. Some companies can have more than 10 different customer personas whereas some companies may only have 3, this really just depends on the nature of your business and your target audience. Spending time on creating these customer personas will help you get a better understanding of your target audience meaning you’ll be better equipped to hit them with more relevant content. An all round win!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 80%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>\r\n&nbsp;','What are customer personas?','','publish','open','open','','what-are-customer-personas','','','2015-08-26 17:57:12','2015-08-26 16:57:12','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=977',0,'post','',0),(982,2,'2015-06-22 16:16:56','2015-06-22 15:16:56','','Pricing & Signup','','publish','open','closed','','start-trial','','','2015-11-05 11:15:18','2015-11-05 10:15:18','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=982',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(983,2,'2015-06-22 19:58:52','2015-06-22 18:58:52','','birdleaf_customer_persona_template_example','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_customer_persona_template_example','','','2015-06-22 19:58:52','2015-06-22 18:58:52','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_template_example.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(984,2,'2015-06-22 19:58:54','2015-06-22 18:58:54','','birdleaf_customer_persona_template_blank','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_customer_persona_template_blank','','','2015-06-30 12:22:52','2015-06-30 11:22:52','',1001,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_template_blank.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(985,2,'2015-06-22 20:30:53','2015-06-22 19:30:53','','birdleaf_customer_persona_cover_image','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_customer_persona_cover_image','','','2015-06-22 20:30:53','2015-06-22 19:30:53','',977,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_cover_image.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(986,3,'2015-08-18 16:16:52','2015-08-18 15:16:52','<div style=\"max-width: 730px; margin: 0 auto;\">\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Using the<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/what-is-a-customer-persona\"> customer persona template</a> will help you understand your current and prospective customers better. This makes it easier for you to tailor your content, messaging, product development, and services to the specific needs and behaviours of different clusters of customers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">You can fill out this customer persona template through research, surveys, and interviews of your target audience. Ideally this would include a mix of customers, prospects, and those outside your contacts database who might align with your target audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Guide to filling out a customer persona template</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The main stumbling block in creating a customer persona is figuring out where you\'ll get all the information you need to make the persona rich enough that it adds value. But there are a few places you can start looking straight away to start gleaning some insights.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Google Analytics</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Google analytics can provide you with a good source of demographical information from your website traffic. In the Audience tab you can filter through Age, Gender, Interests, Location, Technology Preferences and more.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Here is a sample of the information you can recover from google analytics.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-988\" style=\"max-width: 90%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_ga.jpg\" alt=\"birdleaf_customer_persona_ga\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Facebook Insights</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Facebook has the capability for you to create a custom audience by uploading a list of customer information, like customer phone numbers and it will give you an aggregate view on some demographical information similar to google analytics. This can also be helpful in establishing some data points like gender and age.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-989\" style=\"max-width: 90%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_fb.jpg\" alt=\"birdleaf_customer_persona_fb\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Professional Info</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For the professional info you can use Rapportive if you have a small sample set of email addresses to get their linkedIn profile so you can view their current job title and company. However, this process can be pretty slow. If you wanted to do a large sample then a survey using a tool like <a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/\">Survey Monkey</a> or <a class=\"\" href=\"http://www.typeform.com/\">Typeform,</a> or customer intelligence tool like <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/\">birdleaf </a> may be more appropriate and give you some deeper insight.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"> <img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-990\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_rap.jpg\" alt=\"birdleaf_customer_persona_rap\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Problems, Goals &amp; Values</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For the what section of the template, this information is a lot more qualitative and varied so the medium you should use here would ideally be a customer interview. This will allow you to establish what their core pain points are and what their goals and values are.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">During your interviews you should let the customer do all the talking as you will learn most by listening to all their problems and you\'ll more than likely uncover problems that you didn\'t realise your customer has but could be solved by a new feature that going to be released in your product in the next few weeks. You can ask questions like:</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 25px;\">\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Problems</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 50px;\">\r\n	<li class=\"p1\">What are your biggest challenges at the moment?</li>\r\n	<li>Why are these your biggest challenges?</li>\r\n	<li>What are you currently doing to solve these?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Goals</strong>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 50px;\">\r\n	<li>What are you responsible for?</li>\r\n	<li>What would success look like to you?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Values </strong>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 50px;\">\r\n	<li>Where do you go to find out about new products?</li>\r\n	<li>What are your priorities when purchasing?</li>\r\n	<li>What are your biggest objections when purchasing?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">These questions will allow to fill out the what section of the template but it will also allow you to fill out the how part of the template as you\'ll have established that customer personas biggest problem, what they value during the sales process and how they like to be sold to meaning you can tailor your marketing message to address these areas.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Organising Customer Interviews</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For scheduling interviews, it can work best if you target specific people that fit your customer persona which will come from filling out the who section of the template. Here\'s a few tips for getting a higher response rate:</p>\r\n<span style=\"margin-left: 50px;\">\r\n<strong>1)</strong> <b>Stress that it\'s not a sales call: </b>Understandably you\'ll have a lower response rate from customers if they think that you are trying to organise a call so you can up-sell them to a higher pricing tier. Make sure you articulate the purpose of the interview is purely to understand more about your customers.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>2) A clear ask:</strong> People are going to be more likely to say yes if they know exactly what is being asked of them. You will get dramatically lower response rates if there is any ambiguity so make sure you include whether it is a 10-minute call or a 30-minute call.\r\n\r\n<strong>3) Offer an Incentive: </strong>Offering some form of incentive can often increase your response rates. You can offer anything from a free gift card to a free consultation depending on your business.\r\n\r\n<strong>4) Follow up: </strong>don\'t just ask once. You\'d be surprised the response rate you get from the first follow up email. If they don\'t reply after the first email it could be worth following up after a couple of days to remind them as they may have been busy when they received your initial email.\r\n\r\nYou should aim to create between 3-5 customer personas and within each customer persona you should aim to complete between 3-5 interviews to get a good mix of data. Once you\'ve completed your different customer personas it should become clear on the difference between each segment and the different marketing routes you\'ll need to use to acquire a new customer that fits that specific customer persona.\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s1\">If you need any help with developing your customer personas, or if you have further questions, just drop me an email to <a href=\"mailto:scott@birdleaf.io\"><span class=\"s2\">scott@birdleaf.io</span></a> and I’ll be happy to have a chat!</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 80%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>','Tips for creating a customer persona template','','publish','open','open','','customer-persona-template','','','2015-08-26 17:54:36','2015-08-26 16:54:36','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=986',0,'post','',0),(988,2,'2015-06-23 10:39:16','2015-06-23 09:39:16','','birdleaf_customer_persona_ga','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_customer_persona_ga','','','2015-06-23 10:39:16','2015-06-23 09:39:16','',986,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_ga.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(989,2,'2015-06-23 10:44:11','2015-06-23 09:44:11','','birdleaf_customer_persona_fb','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_customer_persona_fb','','','2015-06-23 10:44:11','2015-06-23 09:44:11','',986,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_fb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(990,2,'2015-06-23 10:59:13','2015-06-23 09:59:13','','birdleaf_customer_persona_rap','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_customer_persona_rap','','','2015-06-23 10:59:13','2015-06-23 09:59:13','',986,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_rap.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(991,2,'2015-06-23 12:18:13','2015-06-23 11:18:13','','birdleaf_customer_persona_how_to_create','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_customer_persona_how_to_create','','','2015-06-23 12:18:13','2015-06-23 11:18:13','',986,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_how_to_create.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(994,2,'2015-06-24 15:53:27','2015-06-24 14:53:27','<div align=\"center\">\r\n<h3>FREE CUSTOMER\r\nPERSONA GUIDE FOR YOUR BUSINESS</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<p style=\"color: #86c177; font-size: 120%;\">Segment your target audience to get more out of your marketing efforts. Download now!</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 35px;\">[su_row]\r\n[su_column size=\"1/2\"]\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 115%;\">Building a customer <a href=\"http://searchcrm.techtarget.com/definition/customer-segmentation\" target=\"_blank\">persona</a> for your business really important for your marketing efforts. This customer persona guide will walk you through the process allowing you to improve your lead generation capabilities, create a target sales approach and enhance your product positioning.</p>\r\nThis free customer persona guide will allow you to easily create a customer personas for your business. The guide covers the following:\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">• What a customer persona is</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">• How to create a customer persona</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">• What questions to ask your customers</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 20px;\">• Why a customer persona is important to your business.</p>\r\n[/su_column]\r\n[su_column size=\"1/3\"]<img class=\" size-full wp-image-995 alignleft\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer-persona-guide-cover.jpg\" alt=\"customer-persona-guide-cover\" />\r\n\r\n[mc4wp_form]\r\n\r\n[/su_column]\r\n[/su_row]\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<style>.page-title {visability: hidden; display:none;}</style>','Free Customer Persona Guide For Marketer\'s','','publish','open','open','','free-customer-persona-guide','','','2015-06-30 15:33:46','2015-06-30 14:33:46','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?page_id=994',0,'page','',0),(995,2,'2015-06-24 14:16:42','2015-06-24 13:16:42','','customer-persona-guide-cover','','inherit','open','open','','customer-persona-guide-cover','','','2015-06-24 14:16:42','2015-06-24 13:16:42','',994,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer-persona-guide-cover.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(996,2,'2015-06-24 15:44:55','2015-06-24 14:44:55','','Customer Persona Guide','','inherit','open','open','','customer-persona-guide','','','2015-06-24 15:44:55','2015-06-24 14:44:55','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Customer-Persona-Guide.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(997,2,'2015-06-24 16:07:55','2015-06-24 15:07:55','','customer_persona_banner','','inherit','open','open','','customer_persona_banner','','','2015-06-24 16:07:55','2015-06-24 15:07:55','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1001,3,'2015-08-22 15:41:14','2015-08-22 14:41:14','When it comes to your marketing efforts and deciding on what channels you should focus on it is really important to have a clear picture of your <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/what-is-a-customer-persona\">customer personas</a>. These are fictional, generalized representations of your ‘ideal customers’ designed to help you understand your customers and potential customers better.\r\n\r\nThese cluster of customers should exhibit similar behavioural patterns in their purchasing decisions, use of technology or products, customer service preferences, lifestyle choices, and the like. Therefore how you market to each persona can change drastically depending on the customer segment makeup.\r\n<blockquote style=\"margin-left: 25px;\">A customer<a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/33491/Everything-Marketers-Need-to-Research-Create-Detailed-Buyer-Personas-Template.aspx\"> </a>persona is a semi-fictional representation of your ideal customer based on market research and real data about your existing customers.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/buyer-persona-definition-under-100-sr\" target=\"_blank\">Hubspot</a></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h3><b>The basic customer persona template</b></h3>\r\nCreating your customer personas is quite straightforward, as regardless of your business there are a few common elements that should be included for a customer persona to be as effective as possible.\r\n\r\nA lot of these templates include the same basic information like <strong>who</strong> the person is, <strong>what</strong> problems they have, and <strong>how</strong> to acquire these customers. Here is a quick overview on what you should include in your customer persona template:<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Birdleaf_customer_persona_template_guide.jpg\">\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-1002\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Birdleaf_customer_persona_template_guide.jpg\" alt=\"Birdleaf_customer_persona_template_guide\" width=\"730\" height=\"548\" /></a>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Who?</strong></h4>\r\nHere you\'re summing up common personal and professional demographics. These data points can be very useful when advertising as on a lot of ad networks you can set a lot of demographical filters to target people that match this demographical criteria.\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 75px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Basic demographics</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Age</li>\r\n	<li>Gender</li>\r\n	<li>Location</li>\r\n	<li>Family</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Professional demographics</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Job Title</li>\r\n	<li>Industry</li>\r\n	<li>Company Size</li>\r\n	<li>Company Revenue</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>What?</strong></h4>\r\nUnderstanding this part is key in empathizing with the customer. This relates to more specific traits like their personality, values, interests, and lifestyles. The basic demographics provide you with the ‘who’, whereas the Psychographics provide you with the ‘what’.\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 75px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Problems</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What problems does the customer have that you can solve?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Goals</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What is their main goal motivating them to look for a solution?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Values</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What\'s the customers expectations of your product?</li>\r\n	<li>What are their objections during the buying process?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><b>Why?</b></h4>\r\nThis section of the customer persona is all about your marketing message and how you will acquire new customers that fit the specific customer persona. For each customer persona you have how you explain your product should change along with the route to these customers.\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 75px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Product Benefit</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What benefit does your product offer the customer?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Marketing</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>How will you describe your product?</li>\r\n	<li>What routes will you use to reach these customers?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\nTo be successful at creating you customer persona you need to accurately define who the person is, what their problems and goals are, and how you will explain your marketing message.\r\n<div style=\"max-width: 730px; margin: 0 auto;\">\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Example Customer Persona</h3>\r\nNow that we have the customer persona template here is a sample one. This sample customer persona is for a software company that supplies recruitment software that matches potential candidates to available job roles. They sell to customers across a wide range of industries and company sizes. This is one of their personas for a medium sized technology company.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1003\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Birdleaf_Customer_Persona_example.jpg\" alt=\"customer persona example using a customer persona template\" width=\"730\" height=\"548\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"max-width: 730px; margin: 0 auto;\">\r\n<h3><strong>Guide to filling out a customer persona template</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The main stumbling block in<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/customer-persona-template\"> creating a customer persona</a> is figuring out where you\'ll get all the information you need to make the persona rich enough that it adds value. You can build your customer persona through research, surveys, and interviews of your target audience. Ideally this would include a mix of customers and potential customers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Basic and professional demographical information</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">There are a few places you can start looking straight away to start gleaning some insights. You can use the tools you already use like <a href=\"http://google.ie/analytics/\" target=\"_blank\">google analytics</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/help/341425252616329\" target=\"_blank\">facebook</a>, <a href=\"https://www.intercom.io/\" target=\"_blank\">intercom</a> and many more depending what is in your tool stack.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Google Analytics</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Google analytics can provide you with a good source of demographical information from your website traffic. In the Audience tab you can filter through Age, Gender, Interests, Location, Technology Preferences and more.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Here is a sample of the information you can recover from google analytics.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-988\" style=\"max-width: 90%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_ga.jpg\" alt=\"birdleaf_customer_persona_ga\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Facebook Insights</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Facebook has the capability for you to create a custom audience by uploading a list of customer information, like customer phone numbers and it will give you an aggregate view on some demographical information similar to google analytics. This can also be helpful in establishing some data points like gender and age.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-989\" style=\"max-width: 90%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_fb.jpg\" alt=\"birdleaf_customer_persona_fb\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Professional Info</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For the professional info you can use Rapportive if you have a small sample set of email addresses to get their linkedIn profile so you can view their current job title and company. However, this process can be pretty slow. If you wanted to do a large sample then a survey using a tool like <a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/\">Survey Monkey</a> or <a class=\"\" href=\"http://www.typeform.com/\">Typeform,</a> or customer intelligence tool like <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/\">birdleaf </a> may be more appropriate and give you some deeper insight.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"> <img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-990\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/birdleaf_customer_persona_rap.jpg\" alt=\"birdleaf_customer_persona_rap\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Problems, Goals &amp; Values</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For the what section of the template, this information is a lot more qualitative and varied so the medium you should use here would ideally be a customer interview. This will allow you to establish what their core pain points are and what their goals and values are.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">During your interviews you should let the customer do all the talking as you will learn most by listening to all their problems and you\'ll more than likely uncover problems that you didn\'t realise your customer has but could be solved by a new feature that going to be released in your product in the next few weeks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">It is really important to stick to a set of questions during your customer interviews. If you ask people different questions during each interview it will be really hard to recognise any patterns emerging. Below is a set of questions you can use as a guide. These are generic questions so make sure you tailor them to fit your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 25px;\">\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Problems</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 50px;\">\r\n	<li class=\"p1\">What are your biggest challenges at the moment?</li>\r\n	<li>Why are these your biggest challenges?</li>\r\n	<li>What are you currently doing to solve these?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Goals</strong>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 50px;\">\r\n	<li>What are you responsible for?</li>\r\n	<li>What would success look like to you?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Values </strong>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 50px;\">\r\n	<li>Where do you go to find out about new products?</li>\r\n	<li>What are your priorities when purchasing?</li>\r\n	<li>What are your biggest objections when purchasing?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">These questions will allow to fill out the what section of the template but it will also allow you to fill out the how part of the template as you\'ll have established that customer personas biggest problem, what they value during the sales process and how they like to be sold to meaning you can tailor your marketing message to address these areas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Organising Customer Interviews</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For scheduling interviews, it can work best if you target specific people that fit your customer persona which will come from filling out the who section of the template. Here\'s a few tips for getting a higher response rate:</p>\r\n<strong>1)</strong> <b>Stress that it\'s not a sales call: </b>Understandably you\'ll have a lower response rate from customers if they think that you are trying to organise a call so you can up-sell them to a higher pricing tier. Make sure you articulate the purpose of the interview is purely to understand more about your customers.\r\n\r\n<strong>2) A clear ask:</strong> People are going to be more likely to say yes if they know exactly what is being asked of them. You will get dramatically lower response rates if there is any ambiguity so make sure you include whether it is a 10-minute call or a 30-minute call.\r\n\r\n<strong>3) Offer an Incentive: </strong>Offering some form of incentive can often increase your response rates. You can offer anything from a free gift card to a free consultation depending on your business.\r\n\r\n<strong>4) Follow up: </strong>don\'t just ask once. You\'d be surprised the response rate you get from the first follow up email. If they don\'t reply after the first email it could be worth following up after a couple of days to remind them as they may have been busy when they received your initial email.\r\n\r\nYou should aim to create between 3-5 customer personas and within each customer persona you should aim to complete between 3-5 interviews to get a good mix of data. Once you\'ve completed your different customer personas it should become clear on the difference between each segment and the different marketing routes you\'ll need to use to acquire a new customer that fits that specific customer persona.\r\n<h3><b>Why You Should Have A Customer Personas</b></h3>\r\nAt a high level, developing a strong customer persona will result in more efficient and more cost effective marketing. They allow you to clearly segment your target audience into different groups meaning you can personalize and tailor your marketing for your different segments. For example, by segmenting your customer base into three groups you can send tailored content to each group meaning the content is more relevant and actionable for the end user leading to a better customer experience.\r\n\r\nIt also allows you, the marketer, to build a stronger brand by conveying stronger more relevant messaging and increase your return on investment on your marketing spend by focusing on the channels that will work in acquiring new ‘ideal customers’.\r\n<h3><strong>Takeaways</strong></h3>\r\nThe easiest and most accurate source of information for your customer personas should be your existing customer base. Based on your current customers and what you know about them see if you can fill in data points needed for a rich customer persona. If you can’t fill out everything then the quickest way to fill in the gaps is by surveying or interviewing a random selection of your customers.\r\n\r\nWhen creating your customer personas I suggest starting out with a small amount, like 3 or 4. Some companies can have more than 10 different customer personas whereas some companies may only have 3, this really just depends on the nature of your business and your target audience. Spending time on creating these customer personas will help you get a better understanding of your target audience meaning you’ll be better equipped to hit them with more relevant content. An all round win!\r\n\r\nIf you need any help with developing your customer personas, or if you have any further questions, just drop me an email to <a href=\"mailto:scott@birdleaf.io\">scott@birdleaf.io</a> and I\'ll be happy to have a chat!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>\r\n&nbsp;','Ultimate guide to creating a customer persona','','publish','open','open','','ultimate-customer-persona-guide','','','2015-08-26 17:53:12','2015-08-26 16:53:12','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1001',0,'post','',0),(1002,2,'2015-06-30 12:22:37','2015-06-30 11:22:37','','Birdleaf_customer_persona_template_guide','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_customer_persona_template_guide','','','2015-06-30 12:22:37','2015-06-30 11:22:37','',1001,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Birdleaf_customer_persona_template_guide.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1003,2,'2015-06-30 12:23:33','2015-06-30 11:23:33','','Birdleaf_Customer_Persona_example','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_customer_persona_example','','','2015-06-30 12:24:42','2015-06-30 11:24:42','',1001,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Birdleaf_Customer_Persona_example.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1009,2,'2015-07-20 14:46:15','2015-07-20 13:46:15','For a while now the biggest requested feature from all our customers was the ability to manage multiple lists of emails. Today we\'ve added the ability to quickly create, rename and delete lists of emails from anywhere in Birdleaf :)\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-20-at-13.17.26.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1010\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-20-at-13.17.26-610x227.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-07-20 at 13.17.26\" width=\"300\" height=\"112\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Here\'s how it works:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Click the dropdown at the top of the screen to see the list menu.</li>\r\n	<li>Type in the name of your new list (e.g. \'Top Customers\') and click the green tick.</li>\r\n	<li>You will be brought to the \'<a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/add-emails\">Add Emails</a>\' page to add some emails to your new list. (There\'s help on that <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/troubleshooting-a-list-import\">here</a> if needed.)</li>\r\n	<li>The emails will be added to that list. You can now visit the Analytics and Raw Data pages to see data for the emails in that list.</li>\r\n	<li>From any page, click the drop down menu at the top to switch to a different list. To rename or delete a list just click the pencil or bin icons beside any list name.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe \'All Emails\' list shows every email added to every list you have. This is a special, permanent list that can\'t be deleted or renamed.\r\n\r\n<b><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-20-at-14.20.55.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-1011\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-20-at-14.20.55-610x264.png\" alt=\"Files Added\" width=\"300\" height=\"130\" /></a>Show Added Files</b>\r\n\r\nThe add emails page also now shows you the files have been added to that list in the past, to allow you to quickly see what you\'ve put into each list.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-20-at-14.29.07.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1012\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-20-at-14.29.07-610x195.png\" alt=\"Plan Quota\" width=\"300\" height=\"96\" /></a>Check Your Usage</strong>\r\n\r\nThe \'<a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/add-emails\">Add Emails</a>\' and \'<a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/user/account\">Account</a>\' pages both now show the amount of emails you can add on your current plan, and how much you\'ve added so far between all your lists.\r\n\r\nWhen you first log in to check out multiple lists all your emails added to date will be in a list named \'default\'. Feel free to rename, add-to or delete this as you get started with your own lists.\r\n\r\nAs always, we\'d love to hear your feedback on this, and any ideas on how we can improve even more. Thanks for all the suggestions so far - we\'re hard at work on the next improvements already :)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Manage Multiple Lists Of Emails','','publish','open','open','','manage-multiple-lists-of-emails','','','2015-08-26 17:45:21','2015-08-26 16:45:21','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1009',0,'post','',0),(1010,2,'2015-07-20 13:17:56','2015-07-20 12:17:56','','Screen Shot 2015-07-20 at 13.17.26','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-07-20-at-13-17-26','','','2015-07-20 13:17:56','2015-07-20 12:17:56','',1009,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-20-at-13.17.26.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1011,2,'2015-07-20 14:21:51','2015-07-20 13:21:51','','Files Added','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-07-20-at-14-20-55','','','2015-07-20 14:22:01','2015-07-20 13:22:01','',1009,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-20-at-14.20.55.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1012,2,'2015-07-20 14:31:34','2015-07-20 13:31:34','','Plan Quota','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-07-20-at-14-29-07','','','2015-07-20 14:31:52','2015-07-20 13:31:52','',1009,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-20-at-14.29.07.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1015,2,'2015-08-05 10:41:19','2015-08-05 09:41:19','','birdleaf_homepage','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_homepage','','','2015-08-05 10:41:19','2015-08-05 09:41:19','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/birdleaf_homepage.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1016,2,'2015-08-05 11:28:22','2015-08-05 10:28:22','','1-true-personalization','','inherit','open','open','','1-true-personalization','','','2015-08-05 11:28:22','2015-08-05 10:28:22','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/1-true-personalization.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1017,2,'2015-08-05 13:07:53','2015-08-05 12:07:53','','customer-test','','inherit','