/2015/08/Getting_Started_Step_3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1032,2,'2015-08-10 14:53:27','2015-08-10 13:53:27','','Getting_Started_Step_2','','inherit','open','open','','getting_started_step_2','','','2015-08-10 14:54:18','2015-08-10 13:54:18','',783,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Getting_Started_Step_2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1033,2,'2015-08-10 14:53:29','2015-08-10 13:53:29','','Getting_Started_Step_1','','inherit','open','open','','getting_started_step_1','','','2015-08-10 14:54:00','2015-08-10 13:54:00','',783,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Getting_Started_Step_1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1034,2,'2015-08-10 15:10:33','2015-08-10 14:10:33','','xlsx_format','','inherit','open','open','','xlsx_format','','','2015-08-10 15:10:33','2015-08-10 14:10:33','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/xlsx_format.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1035,2,'2015-08-10 15:10:35','2015-08-10 14:10:35','','xls_format','','inherit','open','open','','xls_format','','','2015-08-10 15:10:35','2015-08-10 14:10:35','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/xls_format.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1036,2,'2015-08-10 15:10:39','2015-08-10 14:10:39','','csv_format','','inherit','open','open','','csv_format','','','2015-08-10 15:10:39','2015-08-10 14:10:39','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/csv_format.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1041,2,'2015-08-26 15:31:43','2015-08-26 14:31:43','','Author_scott','','inherit','open','open','','author_scott','','','2015-08-26 15:31:43','2015-08-26 14:31:43','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Author_scott.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1042,2,'2015-08-26 16:06:33','2015-08-26 15:06:33','','birdleaf_side_bar','','inherit','open','open','','birdleaf_side_bar','','','2015-08-26 16:06:33','2015-08-26 15:06:33','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/birdleaf_side_bar.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1054,3,'2015-09-15 19:13:18','2015-09-15 18:13:18','The only way to minimize marketing waste is to fully understand who your customers are, where we can find them online, and what their buying preferences are when purchasing. <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/what-are-customer-personas\" target=\"_blank\">Persona marketing</a> is nothing new but it\'s become increasingly important to have a deep understanding of your different customer types to maximize your marketing ROI.\r\n\r\nDoing market research on your customers and potential customers can seem like a daunting and time-consuming task but there are plenty of market research tools you can use to automate the whole process at scale. Below we\'ve compiled a list of 13 market research tools that will instantly unlock insights on your customers.\r\n\r\nWe\'ve broken the list into three categories. <a href=\"#survey\">Survey tools</a>, <a href=\"#feedback\">Feedback tools</a>, and <a href=\"#data\">Data tools</a>.\r\n<div id=\"survey\">\r\n<h3><strong>Survey Tools</strong></h3>\r\n<strong>1) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Survey Monkey</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1055\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/survey_monkey_market_research_tools.jpg\" alt=\"Screenshot of Survey Monkey Market Research Tool\" width=\"488\" height=\"313\" />\r\n\r\nFor years Survey Monkey has been the go to survey tool that is packed with loads of features. Whether you want to build a quick 3-question survey or an in-depth highly customized survey, this is a powerful tool for creating detailed surveys that will help you understand the market and consumer preferences.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> Free - <strong> </strong>$99 /mo\r\n\r\n<strong>2) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://www.typeform.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Typeform</a></strong>\r\n\r\nTypeform is really similar to Survey Monkey in that you can built really in-depth surveys that you can send to thousands of people, but the key difference is the end-user experience (people taking the survey). When taking a Typeform survey it feels a lot more intuitive to navigate through than a Survey Monkey survey. For example, survey respondents can navigate through the survey using just their keyboard making the surveys a lot easier to interact with.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"http://www.typeform.com/pricing\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> Free - $20 /mo\r\n\r\n<strong>3) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"http://www.clickinsights.io/\" target=\"_blank\">ClickInsights</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1056\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Clickinsights_market_research_tool.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of Clickinsights Market Research Tool\" width=\"610\" height=\"388\" />\r\n\r\nThis is a really cool, lightweight survey tool! Clickinsights allows you to create really simple email surveys that makes it really easy and fast for someone to respond. All they have to do is simply click on their answer right inside their email.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"http://www.clickinsights.io/#pricing\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> 14-Day Free Trial | $29 - $149 /mo\r\n\r\n<strong>4) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://www.survata.com\" target=\"_blank\">Survata</a></strong>\r\n\r\nOnce you create a survey with Survata they get consumers to answer the survey for you! What\'s really cool is they let you target respondents in 70 countries by age, gender, location, and other custom attributes allowing you to define the exact demographic group you need.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"https://www.survata.com/basic-pricing/\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> $200 - $2000 /mo\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"feedback\">\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><strong>Feedback Tools</strong></h3>\r\n<strong>5) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://www.intercom.io/\" target=\"_blank\">Intercom</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1057\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/intercom_market_research_tool.jpg\" alt=\"Screenshot of Intercom Market Research Tool\" width=\"610\" height=\"320\" />\r\n\r\nIntercom is a customer communication platform that allows you to easily communicate with customers on your website, inside your web and mobile apps, and by email. You can send tailored messages to different customer segments based on their actions within your apps. For instance, if someone has just tried out a new feature in your app for the first time they will get a personalized in-app message asking them what they thought of the new feature.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"https://www.intercom.io/pricing\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> 14-Day Free Trial | $49 - $820 /mo\r\n\r\n<strong>6) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"http://www.crazyegg.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Crazyegg</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1058\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/crazyegg_market_research_tool.jpg\" alt=\"Screenshot of crazyegg market research tool\" width=\"550\" height=\"369\" />\r\n\r\nCrazyegg is a heat map that shows you what your visitors are doing on your website. It highlights the places that your visitors interact with the most, where they click the most and how they  scroll through your website.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"https://www.crazyegg.com/pricing\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> 30 - Day Free Trial | $9 - $99 /mo\r\n\r\n<strong>7) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://www.temper.io/\" target=\"_blank\">Temper</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1059\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/temper_market_research_tool.jpg\" alt=\"Screenshot of temper market research tool\" width=\"610\" height=\"350\" />\r\n\r\nTemper is a really simple user feedback tool. It asks your visitors or customers to simply click on one of three smiley faces related to their feeling on a topic or experience. You can choose where you want your questions to pop up, like on a specific page on your website or an email footer, the choice is yours.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"https://www.temper.io/pricing\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing</a>: $12 - $199 /mo\r\n\r\n<strong>8) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://qualaroo.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Qualaroo</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1060\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/qualaroo_market_research_tool.jpg\" alt=\"Screenshot of Qualaroo Market Research Tool\" width=\"313\" height=\"402\" />\r\n\r\nThis is a really helpful and simple tool. It allows you to add a simple slide-up survey to any page on your website or any point in your application. For example, on your pricing page you can have a survey pop up and ask your visitors what\'s preventing them from purchasing a plan.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"https://qualaroo.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> 14 - Day Free Trial | $63 - $499 /mo\r\n\r\n<strong>9) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://www.hotjar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Hotjar</a></strong>\r\n\r\nHotjar was built optimize conversion rates on your web and mobile sites. The platform gives you a detailed insight of how your visitors interact with your site. You can view heatmaps, run polls and surveys, and the best but is you can record your visitors session to see how they behave on your site. Essentially it\'s like Crazyegg, Survey Monkey and Qualaroo all bundled into one unified solution.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"https://www.hotjar.com/compare-our-plans\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> Free - $89 /mo\r\n<div id=\"data\">\r\n<h3><strong>Data Tools</strong></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<strong>10) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://mixpanel.com\" target=\"_blank\">Mixpanel</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1061\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/mixpanel_market_research_tool.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of Mixpanel Market Research Tool\" width=\"400\" height=\"338\" />\r\n\r\nMixpanel is an awesome tool to understand how your users interact with your application. Instead of tracking page views, which doesn\'t tell us a whole lot, Mixpanel tracks actions. For instance, you can see what feature a specific user uses the most or at what point in your app most of your users drop off. Mixpanel is definitely a must have if you want to easily measure what people are doing in your app on Android, iOS, or web.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"https://mixpanel.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> Free - $2000 /mo\r\n\r\n<strong>11) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://www.kissmetrics.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Kissmetrics</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1062\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/kissmetrics_market_research_tool.jpg\" alt=\"Screenshot of Kissmetrics market research tool\" width=\"610\" height=\"350\" />\r\n\r\nKissmetric is similar to Mixpanel in that it tracks events rather than page views, but it\'s for your website traffic rather than your customers interaction with your application. The product is focused on optimizing the process of turning your website visitors into customers. Moving past pageviews, Kissmetrics allows you to track form completions, behavior across multiple devices, and where most visitors drop off your site before they purchase.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"https://www.kissmetrics.com/pricing\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> 14 - Day Free Trial | $200 - $2000 /mo\r\n\r\n<strong>12) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ads/audience_insights\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook Audience Insights</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1063\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Facebook_market_research_tool.jpg\" alt=\"Screenshot of Facebook Market Research Tool\" width=\"610\" height=\"303\" />\r\n\r\nAudience insights allows you to learn more about your target audience, including aggregate information about location, demographics, interests, and more. Audience Insights is different from Page Insights because it looks at trends about your current or potential customers across Facebook, whereas Page Insights looks at the interactions with your Page (i.e., likes, comments and shares).\r\n\r\n<strong><span id=\"blogprice\">Pricing:</span></strong> Free\r\n\r\n<strong>13) <a id=\"blogtool\" href=\"https://followerwonk.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Followerwonk</a></strong>\r\n\r\nFollowerwonk is similar to Audience Insights for Facebook but for Twitter. You can analyze a user\'s followers to see where their audience is located, what time they are most active at, topics they talk about, and more.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"blogprice\" href=\"https://moz.com/products/pricing\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> Free - $99 /mo (MOZ Pro Account)\r\n<h3><strong>Takeaways</strong></h3>\r\nThe more you know about your audience, the better you\'ll better you\'ll be able to market to your customers and potential customers. Using a mix of these market research tools will allow you to answer more questions about who your target audience is, and how they interact with your website or application.\r\n\r\nHope this list of tools will help you glean important insights about your customers and in turn help you market more efficiently. If I failed to mention any tools or have any questions feel free to share in the comments!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>','13 Must Have Market Research Tools','','publish','open','open','','market-research-tools','','','2015-09-15 19:34:45','2015-09-15 18:34:45','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1054',0,'post','',0),(1055,3,'2015-08-31 16:11:19','2015-08-31 15:11:19','Screenshot of creating a survey in Survey Monkey. Survey Monkey is a free market research tool. ','Survey Monkey Market Research Tool','','inherit','open','closed','','survey_monkey_market_research_tools','','','2015-08-31 16:41:14','2015-08-31 15:41:14','',1054,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/survey_monkey_market_research_tools.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1056,3,'2015-08-31 17:01:55','2015-08-31 16:01:55','Screenshot of a Clickinsights survey. Clickinsights is a free market research tool. ','Clickinsights Market Research Tool','','inherit','open','closed','','clickinsights_market_research_tool','','','2015-08-31 17:03:25','2015-08-31 16:03:25','',1054,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Clickinsights_market_research_tool.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1057,3,'2015-08-31 17:22:11','2015-08-31 16:22:11','Screenshot of creating a in-app message in Intercom. Intercom is a robust market research tool. ','Intercom Market Research Tool','','inherit','open','closed','','intercom_market_research_tool','','','2015-08-31 17:23:47','2015-08-31 16:23:47','',1054,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/intercom_market_research_tool.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1058,3,'2015-08-31 17:27:30','2015-08-31 16:27:30','A screenshot of the crazyegg heatmap in action. Crazyegg is a market research tool for websites.','crazyegg market research tool','','inherit','open','closed','','crazyegg_market_research_tool','','','2015-08-31 17:28:45','2015-08-31 16:28:45','',1054,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/crazyegg_market_research_tool.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1059,3,'2015-08-31 17:31:34','2015-08-31 16:31:34','A screenshot of the temper dashboard. Temper is a market research tool that gives the end user 3 options when responding to survey question ','Temper Market Research Tool','','inherit','open','closed','','temper_market_research_tool','','','2015-08-31 17:33:10','2015-08-31 16:33:10','',1054,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/temper_market_research_tool.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1060,3,'2015-08-31 17:37:20','2015-08-31 16:37:20','A screenshot of Qualaroo in action. Quataroo is a market research tool that pops up a survey to visitors on your website','Qualaroo Market Research Tool','','inherit','open','closed','','qualaroo_market_research_tool','','','2015-08-31 17:38:56','2015-08-31 16:38:56','',1054,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/qualaroo_market_research_tool.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1061,3,'2015-08-31 17:45:13','2015-08-31 16:45:13','A screenshot of a specific users activity feed in Mixpanel. Mixpanel is a free market research tool that tracks users interactions with your application rather than page views.','Mixpanel Market Research Tool','','inherit','open','closed','','mixpanel_market_research_tool','','','2015-08-31 17:46:50','2015-08-31 16:46:50','',1054,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/mixpanel_market_research_tool.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1062,3,'2015-08-31 17:49:13','2015-08-31 16:49:13','A screenshot of Kissmetrics demo dashboard. Kissmetric is a market research tool that tracks your website visitors interactions with your site','kissmetrics market research tool','','inherit','open','closed','','kissmetrics_market_research_tool','','','2015-08-31 17:50:52','2015-08-31 16:50:52','',1054,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/kissmetrics_market_research_tool.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1063,3,'2015-08-31 17:54:14','2015-08-31 16:54:14','A screenshot of facebook audience insights. Audiences insights is a great free market research tool.','Facebook Market Research Tool','','inherit','open','closed','','facebook_market_research_tool','','','2015-08-31 17:55:52','2015-08-31 16:55:52','',1054,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Facebook_market_research_tool.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1066,3,'2015-09-30 16:46:30','2015-09-30 15:46:30','One of the most common marketing automation face offs is Hubspot vs Marketo. Hubspot is touted as the world’s easiest all round marketing automation solution. Marketo, on the other hand, claims that it is the best in class by offering a more customizable solution. Which one should you use? Which one is the better option for your marketing automation needs?\r\n\r\nBoth products offer very similar features and are both really good options. But depending on what you’re looking for one will be better suited for your needs! To help you make a more informed choice we’ve put together a short, concise comparison focusing on the following aspects: system, pricing, interface, customization, reporting, integration, and differentiating features.\r\n<h3><strong>Platform Overview</strong></h3>\r\nMarketos platform is broken down into four distinct modules: Marketing Automation, Consumer Engagement Marketing, Real-time personalization, and Marketing Management. These distinct modules are what allows you create a custom solution for your needs. These modules can be purchased separately, or combined to create a more unified system.\r\n\r\nHubspots platform on the other hand is an all-in-one unified system, meaning you have full access to all of Hubspots features and capabilities through a single system. In terms of customization, Hubspot recently announced a wealth of pre-built <a href=\"http://www.hubspot.com/products/integrations\">integrations</a> with popular business apps to allowing you to plug into other tools your company uses.\r\n<h3><strong>Pricing</strong></h3>\r\nAs Marketos is split into 4 distinct modules they are all individually priced in tiers depending on what features you need. Entry level tiers start at $895 /mo and the minimum contract is 12-months. Regardless of which modules you use the pricing is based on you not having more than 10,000 contacts in your database. If you\'re fortunate enough to have more than 10,000 contacts you\'ll have to pay extra regardless of which tier you are on.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1080\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Hubspot-vs-marketo-pricing.jpg\" alt=\"Hubspot vs marketo pricing\" width=\"610\" height=\"380\" />\r\n\r\nHubspots pricing is a lot more straight forward. The entry level package starts at $200 /mo and the minimum contract is also 12-months. The tiers are differentiated based on features and volume of contacts in your database. The entry level package allows you to have 100 contacts in your database and each additional 1K of contacts will cost you $100 /mo. In addition to Hubspot offering cheaper entry level pricing they now offer a free 30-day trial so you can test drive the platform.\r\n<h3><strong>Ease Of Use</strong></h3>\r\nSince Marketo has separate modules and specialises in custom solutions for enterprises they platform may require more IT knowledge to operate. However, if you have a marketer that has basic technical skills Marketo might be the favourable option due to the depth of features and customization it offers.\r\n\r\nHubspot on the other hand is a lot more intuitive to use. The platform gives you simple access to its wide range of marketing functions. Its big list of integrations also makes it easy to make sure all your other tools are kept up to date with contacts in your database.\r\n<h3><strong>Reporting</strong></h3>\r\nBoth Hubspot and Marketo have closed-loop reporting as standard. This allows marketers and managers to track campaign progress to identify how prospects are moving through the sales funnel - from first contact to a closed sale. Both platforms provides you with enough data what terms brought them to your site, who the best prospects are and what pages they visit.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1081\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/hubspot-vs-marketo-analytics.jpg\" alt=\"hubspot-vs-marketo-analytics\" width=\"700\" height=\"375\" />\r\n\r\nMarketo offers slightly more advanced and customizable reporting. One really power element of Marketo\'s reporting is the Success Path Analyser. This allows you to see the correlation between marketing efforts and revenue fluctuation over time. This means you can perform predictive analytics and modelling based on digital behaviour patterns, content preferences, and firmographics.\r\n<h3><strong>Integrations</strong></h3>\r\nTo track and report on the full sales cycle - from when someone becomes an initial lead to a paying customer – marketing automation software needs to integrate with your CRM system. Along with other applications you use in your marketing and sales process. Both Marketo and Hubspot have a lot of integrations. Some <a href=\"http://bracketlabs.com/blog/2014/8/5/what-is-a-native-salesforce-app\">native</a> (meaning the platforms seamlessly exchange data with each other) and some provided by third party services.\r\n\r\nMarketo has native integrations with Salesforce and Microsoft Dynamics CRM.  Marketo also has a lot of third party integrations with a wide range of applications which you can check out <a href=\"http://launchpoint.marketo.com\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.\r\n\r\nHubspot recently announced a whole heap of <a href=\"http://www.hubspot.com/products/integrations\" target=\"_blank\">new integrations</a>.  Hubspot has its own <a href=\"http://www.hubspot.com/crm\" target=\"_blank\">CRM</a> platform which is built on-top of their core product, but they also have a native integrations with Salesforce.\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Key Differentiators </strong></h3>\r\nThere is on key differentiator between the services. Simply put Hubspot is more tailored towards attracting more visitors to your website whereas Marketo is more focused on nurturing your leads.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1083 size-full\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/hubspot-vs-marketo-comparison-image.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"375\" />\r\n\r\nMarketo can be viewed more as a engagement marketing platform that focuses on nurturing your leads through the sales funnel with a focus on automated emails, lead scoring, and segmentation. But it doesn\'t necessary solve the problem of getting more visitors to your website.\r\n\r\nHubspot on the other hands an inbound marketing system that uses blogging, SEO and social tools to attract visitors to your website. Once you attract visitors to your site they have tools designed to convert those folks into leads and customers using automation and personalized content.\r\n<h3><strong>Conclusion</strong></h3>\r\nThere isn\'t too much between the two platforms. If you\'re a small to mid sized business looking to bring more visitors to your website and nurture leads without the high-level learning curve of enterprise software then Hubspot could be a better fit. But if you\'re a larger B2B company looking for a more tailored solution that really focus on engaging with prospects through a long sales cycle then Marketo might better align with your needs.\r\n\r\nIf you are still undecided you should check out what their customers are saying. You can get hundreds of reviews in nearly all categories and comparisons on <a href=\"http://www.g2crowd.com/\">G2Crowd</a> and <a href=\"http://www.trustradius.com/\">TrustRadius</a>.','Hubspot Vs Marketo - Battle of the Marketing Automation Platforms','','publish','open','open','','hubspot-vs-marketo-battle-of-the-marketing-automation-platforms','','','2015-09-30 17:29:35','2015-09-30 16:29:35','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1066',0,'post','',0),(1070,3,'2015-09-15 14:45:30','2015-09-15 13:45:30','','market_research_tools_cover','','inherit','open','closed','','market_research_tools_cover','','','2015-09-15 14:45:30','2015-09-15 13:45:30','',1054,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/market_research_tools_cover.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1074,3,'2015-09-18 17:20:06','2015-09-18 16:20:06','','hubspot-vs-marketo-cover','','inherit','open','closed','',