her open rates, and 24% experienced greater revenue.</strong>\" How? Email marketing segmentation allows you to send more targeted and relevant emails to your different <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/what-are-customer-personas\">customer types</a> thus improving your results.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1112\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email_Marketing_Segmentation_Data.jpg\" alt=\"Email Marketing Segmentation Data\" width=\"700\" height=\"222\" />\r\n\r\nThere are a few reasons why an effective email marketing segmentation strategy can yield great results. In this post we\'ll go through the reason you should be segmenting your email list by highlighting the benefits and a couple of examples.\r\n<h3><strong>Not Every Customer Is The Same</strong></h3>\r\nThis might seem obvious but is often overlooked when it comes to email marketing. A lot of companies adopt a \'One Size Fits All\' framework for their email marketing. This holistic \"<a href=\"https://emailexperience.org/2014/12/the-5-stages-of-email-segmentation-sophistication-how-evolved-are-you/\">Batch and Blast</a>\" approach often results in generic emails which make it difficult for the recipient to derive any real value from. While some of them will respond to the promotional emails, the majority of recipients will ignore the email meaning you\'ll have sub-par results from your email marketing. Bottom-line, there is no such thing as an effective all-encompassing message that interests everyone.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1113\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/5_stages_of_email_marketing_segmentation.jpg\" alt=\"Stages of email marketing segmentation\" width=\"984\" height=\"784\" />\r\n\r\nBy segmenting your email list you have the ability to send more relevant content  that aligns to each segment of your audience. This maximizes the chances of converting as many potential customers as possible. For segmentation to be successful it is crucial that you identify these different <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/ultimate-customer-persona-guide\">customer personas</a> and appeal to these different groups.\r\n\r\nOnce you develop and define your different customer personas, segmenting your subscriber base becomes much more understandable and easier. By identifying three or four generic personas and addressing the needs of each subsection will make your segmentation more effective.\r\n<h3><strong>People Are At Different Stages In The Sales Cycle</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">When doing email marketing it\'s important to bear in mind that each contact on your email marketing list are at varied stages of the sales cycle. As a result they will require different messages depending at what stage they are at.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For example, someone who has just subscribed to your newsletter is at a very different stage than someone who has downloaded a few ebooks and had a demo of your product. To effectively target and convert your potential customers you will need to understand your email list and what stage each contact is at.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1116\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email_marketing_segmentation_sales_cycle.jpg\" alt=\"email marketing segmentation sales cycle\" width=\"500\" height=\"297\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">By identifying what stages people are at in the sales cycle it will allow you to separate those contacts that are actively looking for a solution to their problem, and those that are just interested in learning but who have no intention to buy. Making this distinction will allow you to send the different type of contacts more relevant, tailored content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Email Marketing Segmentation Works</strong></h3>\r\n<strong>Bottom-line: </strong>you should use email marketing segmentation because it\'s been proven to dramatically improve your email marketing results.\r\n\r\nThe results vary massively between a segmented and a non-segmented lists. For example, MailChimp reported its segmentation users saw a <a href=\"http://mailchimp.com/resources/research/effects-of-list-segmentation-on-email-marketing-stats/\">75.94% higher click-through rate</a> than their non-segmented list users.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1115\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email_marketing_segmentation_statistics.jpg\" alt=\"email marketing segmentation statistics\" width=\"649\" height=\"358\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sxsw.com/\">SXSW</a> used email marketing segmentation to <a href=\"https://www.campaignmonitor.com/blog/customers/2015/08/how-sxsw-uses-email-segmentation/\">increase subscribers by 140%</a>. By using segmentation, they were able to target their subscribers with the most relevant information based on how they interact with SXSW.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.totes-isotoner.com/\">Totes&gt;&gt;ISOTONER</a> increased<a href=\"http://bronto.com/customers/success-stories/totes-isotoner#.VkHXXBWLQzW\"> email-driven revenue by 7,000% </a>in 14 months by implementing an effective email marketing segmentation strategy.\r\n\r\nAs you can see, all the signs indicate that segmenting your email list is the way to go.\r\n<h3><strong>Takeaways</strong></h3>\r\nIf you want to be getting the best results possible from your email marketing you need to be segmenting your list. Without segmentation, it\'s really hard to engage your subscribers and improve your conversion rates.\r\n\r\nCreating an effective email marketing segmentation strategy starts with understanding your audience better and what stage they are at in the sales cycle. By understanding these two aspects you\'ll be able to serve them better and increase the chances you will increase your conversion rates and revenue.\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>','Why email marketing segmentation matters','','publish','open','open','','why-email-marketing-segmentation-matters','','','2015-11-11 18:04:39','2015-11-11 17:04:39','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1111',0,'post','',0),(1112,2,'2015-11-11 16:18:12','2015-11-11 15:18:12','Image containing email marketing segmentation data.','Email_Marketing_Segmentation_Data','','inherit','open','closed','','email_marketing_segmentation_data','','','2015-11-11 16:19:11','2015-11-11 15:19:11','',1111,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email_Marketing_Segmentation_Data.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1113,2,'2015-11-11 16:29:50','2015-11-11 15:29:50','Image that goes through the 5 stages of email marketing segmentation','5_stages_of_email_marketing_segmentation','','inherit','open','closed','','5_stages_of_email_marketing_segmentation','','','2015-11-11 16:30:41','2015-11-11 15:30:41','',1111,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/5_stages_of_email_marketing_segmentation.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1114,2,'2015-11-11 16:43:42','2015-11-11 15:43:42','','email_marketing_segmentation_cover','','inherit','open','closed','','email_marketing_segmentation_cover','','','2015-11-11 16:43:42','2015-11-11 15:43:42','',1111,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email_marketing_segmentation_cover.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1115,2,'2015-11-11 17:01:49','2015-11-11 16:01:49','An image containing statistics claiming the benefits of email marketing segmentation ','email_marketing_segmentation_statistics','','inherit','open','closed','','email_marketing_segmentation_statistics','','','2015-11-11 17:02:40','2015-11-11 16:02:40','',1111,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email_marketing_segmentation_statistics.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1116,2,'2015-11-11 17:07:07','2015-11-11 16:07:07','Image containing the different stages of the sales cycle for email marketing segmentation','email_marketing_segmentation_sales_cycle','','inherit','open','closed','','email_marketing_segmentation_sales_cycle','','','2015-11-11 17:07:57','2015-11-11 16:07:57','',1111,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email_marketing_segmentation_sales_cycle.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1119,3,'2015-11-16 20:00:13','2015-11-16 19:00:13','In a previous post we went through the importance of having a email<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/why-email-marketing-segmentation-matters\" target=\"_blank\"> marketing segmentation strategy </a>in place. Despite the common argument that email is dying, it is still one of the top performing channels for acquiring and retaining customers.\r\n\r\nSegmenting lists will help you more easily target your customers. It will allow you to send email content to your subscribers that is tailored to their wants and needs, which will drastically improve your open and click-through and conversion rates.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1121\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-list-segmentation-results.jpg\" alt=\"how to segment your email list results\" width=\"600\" height=\"421\" />\r\n\r\nIn this post we\'ll go through how to segment your email list so you can start achieving higher conversion rates.\r\n<h3><b>What You\'ll Need</b></h3>\r\nSegmenting your email list can seem like a daunting challenge but it honestly doesn\'t take much to get it started. You\'ll just need to commit some time to the planning process to make sure you can effectively implement your plans.\r\n\r\nTo start segmenting your email list you\'ll need some basic customer information. This can be anything, such as their gender or location. These basic data points are enough to get you started, so don\'t worry if you limited data on your customers. As your segmentation strategy evolves and you identify the crucial data points you need and start collecting this information.\r\n\r\nYou shouldn\'t need any additional tools to get started if you\'re already using an email marketing tool. Most email marketing tools, like <a href=\"http://mailchimp.com\" target=\"_blank\">Mailchimp</a> or <a href=\"http://www.aweber.com\" target=\"_blank\">AWeber</a>, make it really simple to organise your segments automatically.\r\n<h3><strong>Different Data Types For Segmentation</strong></h3>\r\nThere are many for you to segment your customer list to provide more relevant content to your subscribers. In reality, any data that you can tie back to a subscriber could be a segment. Each business is going to want to segment their subscribers using different data points. For example, an e-commerce company may choose to Gender and Age to segment their subscribers. While on the other hand a B2B software company may choose to segment based on Industry and Job Role. Here are some samples of the types of segmentation you can implement: Demographic, Behavioural, and Purchase Cycle.\r\n<h5 id=\"blogsubhead\"><strong>Demographical Data</strong></h5>\r\nDemographic data is any personal characteristics of a person, such as age,  gender, job etc. One of the main advantages of demographic segmentation is that the information you need is readily available for you, and you can group subscribers together without getting specific. That being said, demographical segmentation can be highly effective.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1123\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/how-to-segment-your-email-list-demographic-data-exampe.jpg\" alt=\"how to segment your email marketing list demographic data example\" width=\"800\" height=\"393\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>Emails sent by Johnny Cupcakes segmented by gender.</i></p>\r\nClothing brand Johnny Cupcakes launched a segmented email marketing campaign for the product launch of its new baseball T-shirts. By simply segmenting their email list into male and female subscribers they saw a <a href=\"http://www.marketingsherpa.com/article/case-study/social-behavioral-email-segmentation\">141% increase in revenue per campaign</a>. This massive increase in revenue resulted from a 42% increase in clickthrough rate and 123% more conversions.\r\n\r\nDepending on your target market you can try using these demographic groups to segment your list:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Gender</strong> - like the example above. This works really well for e-commerce fashion companies. If you are selling to both men and women then generic email marketing will be a total flop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Location </strong>- if you want to offer free shipping across the U.S, you can\'t be marketing the coupon code to this customers living in Canada. Knowing where your customers live and marketing to their location is essential to building a positive email reputation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Job Role </strong>- this is definitely more applicable for B2B businesses. Segmenting subscribers based on job role can be really effective. For instance, the sales pitch you would send a Sales Rep would be different then that you would send the VP of Sales.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Industry  </strong>-  different industries should be approached and marketed differently. For example, if you have three different customerKnowing your customer\'s industry may allow you to add a level of personalization or authority to your content. This is more impactful for B2B businesses.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5 id=\"blogsubhead\"><strong>Behavioural Data</strong></h5>\r\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\r\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\r\n<div class=\"column\">\r\n\r\nBehavioural data includes any defined interactions with your product or service: purchase history, buying frequency, in-app behaviours, usage rate and so on.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1124\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/how-to-segment-your-email-list-behavioural-data-exampe.jpg\" alt=\"how to segment your email list behavioural data example\" width=\"900\" height=\"695\" />\r\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\r\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\r\n<div class=\"column\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Email sent to best customers identified by purchasing data.</em></p>\r\nOnline mens reatiler <a href=\"http://onwardreserve.com\" target=\"_blank\">Onward Reserve</a> segmented customers based on purchase data that increased their conversions by 233% and revenue by 278%. By leveraging the purchasing data at their disposal Onward Reserve were able to segment each subscriber into one of four customer types: best customers (at least 3 purchases), non-purchasers, churning customers and other. These distinct groups were sent different messages tailored to their previous on-site behaviour.\r\n\r\nTry using these behaviuoral segments to target people based on their interactions with your product or service:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>What they purchase</strong> - Amazon does an amazing job of this with their \"You bought this, so you might like this” upsell. By knowing someones past purchases you can use that information to send them emails catered to that which interests them. This will lead to more purchases and a longer lifetime value.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Purchase frequency </strong>- some people may purchase every week whereas some subscribers may be repeat customers but only purchase once a year. By looking at each customer’s buying behaviour JAM Paper\'s team calculated the average time between orders for each customer and began sending the “lapsed purchase” email once each person passed their individual threshold. This tactic yielded a <a href=\"http://sherpablog.marketingsherpa.com/email-marketing/list-segmentation-tips/\" target=\"_blank\">45% conversion rate</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>What they do in your product</strong> - this allows you to send tailored messages to your subscribers based on their interaction with your website or application. Triggered messages are a great way to engage with your customers without effort. For example, a lot of e-commerce companies will target subscribers who added a product to the shopping cart but didn\'t complete the purchase. If they haven\'t completed the purchase within 24 hours, an email is triggered targeted toward that specific target group.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Free vs paid users</strong> - for both segments of users you have very different objectives. Your goal with non-paying users is to convert as many as possible. Whereas your goal with paid users is to retain as many as possible.With that in mind you\'ll probably send a lot of upgrade pitches to your free users, and for your paid users you will send them tailored messages to keep them engaged in the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h5 id=\"blogsubhead\"><strong>Position In Sales Cycle</strong></h5>\r\nEach one of your subscribers is inevitably going to be at a different point in your sales cycle. By segmenting in this way you can formulate and tailor your marketing communication to increase the likelihood that each prospect will engage with your emails and move from one stage of the sales cycle to the next.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1126\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/how-to-segment-your-email-list-sales-cycle-exampe.jpg\" alt=\"how to segment your email marketing list sales cycle example\" width=\"800\" height=\"351\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Segmenting customer based on position in sales cycle.</em></p>\r\nNews agency PR Newswire <a href=\"http://www.marketingsherpa.com/article/case-study/shortened-sales-cycle\" target=\"_blank\">shortened its sales cycle by 30% </a>by aligning their email content to each stage of the buyers journey. As you watch a lead move through the sales funnel you will be able to pinpoint the right time for your sales team to get in touch directly. This will allow you to minimize the likelyhood of a Sales Rep wasting time on unqualified leads.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Top of the funnel </strong>- for prospects at the top of the sales funnel content should be educational and product-neutral. Think about white papers and content that\'s focused on industry relevant topics, not your product. Prospects at this stage might not even be aware that they have a fixable problem, so identifying this problem should be your focus for this stage.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Middle of the funnel </strong>- as prospects move into the middle of the funnel your content should get a bit more specific. The aim of the game at this stage is to get your prospects thinking about the advantages of having your product. So you can send out case studies about how a similar business has the same problem and this is how they fixed it using our product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Bottom of the funnel </strong>- once a prospect reaches the bottom of the funnel you need to start actively selling them your product. At this stage they\'re going to be well educated on the problem area and are potentially looking for a solution.  Getting a sales rep to contact the prospect and go through a buyers guide and implementation strategy is really important.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Takeaways</strong></h3>\r\nEach one of your subscribers, prospect, customers are different in some way. For this reason it\'s really important to segment your email marketing list in an attempt to tailor your messages so they are relevant to the recipient.\r\n\r\nHow you segment your list will depend on your target audience and what level of data you have on each subscriber. To start maximising the impact of your email marketing you can segment your list using demographic, behavioural, or sales cycle data.\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>','How to segment your email list for higher conversion rates','','publish','open','open','','how-to-segment-your-email-list-for-higher-conversion-rates','','','2015-11-19 15:58:46','2015-11-19 14:58:46','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1119',0,'post','',0),(1121,2,'2015-11-15 23:11:50','2015-11-15 22:11:50','Image containing the results of segmenting your email list','email-list-segmentation-results','','inherit','open','closed','','email-list-segmentation-results','','','2015-11-15 23:13:45','2015-11-15 22:13:45','',1119,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-list-segmentation-results.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1123,3,'2015-11-16 13:34:11','2015-11-16 12:34:11','Image containing an example of how to segment your email list using demographic data','how-to-segment-your-email-list-demographic-data-exampe','','inherit','open','closed','','how-to-segment-your-email-list-demographic-data-exampe','','','2015-11-16 13:35:27','2015-11-16 12:35:27','',1119,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/how-to-segment-your-email-list-demographic-data-exampe.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1124,3,'2015-11-16 19:23:31','2015-11-16 18:23:31','Image contains an example of how to segment your email list with behavioural data','how-to-segment-your-email-list-behavioural-data-exampe','','inherit','open','closed','','how-to-segment-your-email-list-behavioural-data-exampe','','','2015-11-16 19:24:44','2015-11-16 18:24:44','',1119,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/how-to-segment-your-email-list-behavioural-data-exampe.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1125,4,'2015-11-20 13:40:31','2015-11-20 12:40:31','Our <a href=\"http://zapier.com\" target=\"_blank\">Zapier</a> integration is here! One of the top requests for Birdleaf has been to integrate with 3rd party tools. People wanted a way for emails to be automatically added to Birdleaf, and insights to be automatically exported to other tools. We chose to integrate with Zapier first, as this connects Birdleaf to the 500+ services they have integrations with.\r\n\r\nSo, from today, you can connect Birdleaf to <a href=\"http://www.salesforce.com\" target=\"_blank\">Salesforce</a>, <a href=\"http://mailchimp.com\" target=\"_blank\">Mailchimp</a>, <a href=\"https://www.intercom.io\" target=\"_blank\">Intercom</a>, <a href=\"http://www.hubspot.com\" target=\"_blank\">HubSpot</a> and <a href=\"https://zapier.com/zapbook\" target=\"_blank\">many, many more</a>!\r\n\r\nTo get started:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>First you\'ll need to have a Zapier account - you can sign up <a href=\"https://zapier.com/sign-up/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>Next you\'ll need your unique Zapier key from Birdleaf (you\'ll add this key in Zapier to allow them to connect to you Birdleaf account). To get your key, visit your <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/user/account\" target=\"_blank\">Account page</a>, and click \'Generate Key\' (see picture below).<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Generate-Key.png\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1143 size-large\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Generate-Key-930x109.png\" alt=\"Click \'Generate Key\' to get your unique Zapier key.\" width=\"930\" height=\"109\" /></a>You now have a unique key to connect your Birdleaf account to Zapier.<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Copy-Your-Zapier-Key1.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1145\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Copy-Your-Zapier-Key1-930x109.png\" alt=\"Your Birdleaf Zapier Key\" width=\"930\" height=\"109\" /></a></li>\r\n	<li>Finally, our Zapier integration is still in private beta, so you\'ll need to click the big button below to get access to Birdleaf in Zapier. (We\'ll also send you an access link in a message when you generate your Zapier key in the Account page, so you have a copy).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[su_button url=\"http://bit.ly/blzapinvt\" target=\"blank\" style=\"flat\" color=\"#ffffff\" wide=\"yes\" center=\"yes\" radius=\"round\" icon=\"icon: arrow-right\"]Add Birdleaf To My Zapier Account Now![/su_button]\r\n\r\nNow you\'re ready to get started! If you\'ve used Zapier before, you can connect Birdleaf just like an other app. If you need some help getting started, we have a walkthrough on <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/connecting-birdleaf-to-mailchimp-using-zapier\" target=\"_blank\">how to connect Birdleaf to Mailchimp using Zapier here</a> as an example.\r\n\r\nWe\'d love to hear any feedback you have when using it to help us improve our integration going forward. If you have any questions feel free to comment below, send us <a href=\"mailto:support@birdleaf.io\" target=\"_blank\">an email</a>, or drop us a message in the in-app support chat. Enjoy!','How To Use Zapier With Birdleaf','','publish','open','open','','how-to-use-zapier-with-birdleaf','','','2015-11-24 11:14:30','2015-11-24 10:14:30','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1125',0,'post','',0),(1126,3,'2015-11-17 15:39:32','2015-11-17 14:39:32','Image containing an example of how to segment your email list using sales cycle data','how-to-segment-your-email-list-sales-cycle-exampe','','inherit','open','closed','','how-to-segment-your-email-list-sales-cycle-exampe','','','2015-11-17 15:40:15','2015-11-17 14:40:15','',1119,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/how-to-segment-your-email-list-sales-cycle-exampe.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1128,3,'2015-11-17 16:26:39','2015-11-17 15:26:39','How to segment your email list for higher conversion rates cover image','How to segment your email list for higher conversion rates cover','','inherit','open','closed','','how-to-segment-your-email-list-for-higher-conversion-rates-cover','','','2015-11-17 16:26:55','2015-11-17 15:26:55','',1119,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/How-to-segment-your-email-list-for-higher-conversion-rates-cover.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1130,3,'2015-11-18 19:05:57','2015-11-18 18:05:57','It’s common knowledge that <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/why-email-marketing-segmentation-matters\">segmenting your email-marketing lists</a> helps you get better open and click rates, which ultimately leads to increased revenue. By narrowing your focus and sending tailored messages to targeted groups within your lists, your recipients will find your campaigns more relevant—and relevant campaigns get better results.\r\n\r\nAccording to <a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/13879/Segment-Your-Email-List-To-Increase-Open-Rates-Data.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">eMarketer</a>, \"39% of marketers who segmented their email lists experienced higher open rates, and 24% experienced greater revenue.\"\r\n\r\nIf utilised correctly, email can convert better than any other channel. A report found that for every $1 you invest in email you\'ll get a <a href=\"http://www.business2community.com/email-marketing/14-email-marketing-statistics-you-need-to-know-0513966#RT5mCrlEHA4EQHeJ.97\" target=\"_blank\">$40 return</a>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1131\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-data.jpg\" alt=\"email segmentation case studies ROI data\" width=\"800\" height=\"368\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Email can represent a 4000% ROI</em></p>\r\nIn this post we\'ll go through five highly effective email segmentation case studies. Each case study is different. Some companies segment by behavioural data whilst others  segment by demographical data.\r\n<h3>Clothing brand increased revenue by 141% per campaign</h3>\r\nClothing brand Johnny Cupcakes launched a segmented email marketing campaign for the product launch of its new baseball T-shirts.\r\n\r\nBy simply segmenting their email list into male and female subscribers they saw a <a href=\"http://www.marketingsherpa.com/article/case-study/social-behavioral-email-segmentation\">141% increase in revenue per campaign</a>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1123\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/how-to-segment-your-email-list-demographic-data-exampe.jpg\" alt=\"how to segment your email marketing list demographic data example\" width=\"800\" height=\"393\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><i>Emails sent by Johnny Cupcakes segmented by gender.</i></em></p>\r\nThis basic demographic segmentation resulted in:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>42% increase in clickthrough rates</li>\r\n	<li>123% increase in conversion rate</li>\r\n	<li>141% increase in revenue per campaign</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Fashion store increases sales by 550%</h3>\r\nA fashion store identified a segment of customers who had made one or <a href=\"https://canopylabs.com/blog/increasing-e-mail-based-sales-by-5-5-times-a-case-study-in-segmentation\" target=\"_blank\">two significant purchases</a>, but don\'t visit or buy on a regular basis.\r\n\r\nThis allowed the fashion store to send this segment of their customer base an email thanking them for their past purchase and inviting them to purchase again with a small tailored offer in an attempt to re-active them.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-fashion-co.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1132\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-fashion-co.jpg\" alt=\"email segmentation case studies ROI at a Fashion Store\" width=\"800\" height=\"481\" /></a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>Segmented vs Generic Email Campaigns</i></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This basic behavioural (purchase history) segmentation resulted in:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>41% increase in open rates</li>\r\n	<li>41% increase in clickthrough rates</li>\r\n	<li>550% increase in purchases per campaign</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>E-commerce site increased CTR by 410%</h3>\r\n<a href=\"https://doggyloot.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Doggyloot</a> is a flash sale site that helps dog owners spoil their beloved canines. The company segments and personalizes emails based on \"doggy data,\" not people data.\r\n\r\nThe company segments their customers into <a href=\"http://www.marketingsherpa.com/article/case-study/email-personalization-ctr-ecommerce-site#\" target=\"_blank\">3 groups based on dog size</a>. Small, medium, and large. This segmentation is based on the logic that it doesn\'t make sense to offer a 10-pound bone to a five-pound dog. This basic level of segmentation yields some impressive results.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1133 size-full\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-doggyloot.png\" alt=\"email segmentation case studies ROI at doggyloot\" width=\"1106\" height=\"802\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Email sent to customers that own large dogs</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This basic demographical (dog size) segmentation resulted in:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>10% increase in open rate</li>\r\n	<li>410% increase in click through rates</li>\r\n	<li>13% increase in revenue per campaign</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>E-commerce site increased revenue by 278%</h3>\r\nOnline men\'s retailer <a href=\"http://onwardreserve.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Onward Reserve</a> segmented customers based on purchase data that increased their <a href=\"http://web.windsorcircle.com/Portals/254322/images/windsor-circle-case-study-onward-reserve.pdf?submissionGuid=48f343b6-0956-41b9-9a8f-b1a400e9f5bf\" target=\"_blank\">conversions by 233%</a>.\r\n\r\nBy leveraging the purchasing data at their disposal Onward Reserve were able to segment each subscriber into one of four customer types: best customers (at least 3 purchases), non-purchasers, churning customers and other. These distinct groups were sent different messages tailored to their previous on-site behaviour.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1134\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-onward-reserve.png\" alt=\"email segmentation case studies ROI at onward reserve\" width=\"709\" height=\"797\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Email onward reserve sends to \'best customers\'</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This basic behavioural (purchase frequency) segmentation resulted in:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>41% increase in open rates</li>\r\n	<li>183% increase in click through rates</li>\r\n	<li>278% increase in revenue</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3> Multi-channel retail store increased open rates by 40%</h3>\r\nSwayChic is the e-commerce store for a California-based women’s fashion retailer, Sway. The brand features six brick-and-mortar stores and it\'s through these stores Sway\'s associates organically collect customer email addresses.\r\n\r\nThey created new campaigns which were segmented into different time slots as well as tailoring the emails based on their customers historic purchase behaviour. For example, one-time buyer, frequent buyers, and buyers who were no longer engaged.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.marketingsherpa.com/article/case-study/lift-average-open-rate-segmentation\" target=\"_blank\">In creating this campaign</a>, they used historical data to test different attributes, such as days with the highest open rates, past purchases, and time of actual conversions.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1135\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-Swaychic.jpg\" alt=\"email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-Swaychic\" width=\"800\" height=\"683\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Email targeted at customers that we no longer engaged</em></p>\r\nSwayChic\'s segmented campaign resulted in:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>40% increase in open rates</li>\r\n	<li>100% increase in click through rates</li>\r\n	<li>200% increase in revenue for each campaign</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Takeaways</h3>\r\nSegmenting email campaigns can help online business boost both relative and absolute sales without requiring a significant time investment. There are many other examples of targeted campaigns that are made possible through centralizing data and predictive analytics. Please let us know if you have come across some other killer email segmentation case studies.\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>','5 killer email segmentation case studies','','publish','open','open','','5-killer-email-segmentation-case-studies','','','2015-11-19 17:08:12','2015-11-19 16:08:12','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1130',0,'post','',0),(1131,2,'2015-11-18 17:34:14','2015-11-18 16:34:14','Image containing the ROI of email marketing','email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-data','','inherit','open','closed','','email-segmentation-case-studies-roi-data','','','2015-11-18 17:35:51','2015-11-18 16:35:51','',1130,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-data.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1132,2,'2015-11-19 12:23:23','2015-11-19 11:23:23','This image contains the results of email segmentation for a fashion company','email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-fashion co','','inherit','open','closed','','email-segmentation-case-studies-roi-fashion-co','','','2015-11-19 12:25:36','2015-11-19 11:25:36','',1130,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-fashion-co.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1133,2,'2015-11-19 13:05:34','2015-11-19 12:05:34','Image containing a segmented email that doggyloot sends to dog owners','email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-doggyloot','','inherit','open','closed','','email-segmentation-case-studies-roi-doggyloot','','','2015-11-19 13:06:50','2015-11-19 12:06:50','',1130,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-doggyloot.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1134,2,'2015-11-19 13:39:22','2015-11-19 12:39:22','','email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-onward reserve','','inherit','open','closed','','email-segmentation-case-studies-roi-onward-reserve','','','2015-11-19 13:39:41','2015-11-19 12:39:41','',1130,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-onward-reserve.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1135,2,'2015-11-19 16:27:36','2015-11-19 15:27:36','','email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-Swaychic','','inherit','open','closed','','email-segmentation-case-studies-roi-swaychic','','','2015-11-19 16:28:01','2015-11-19 15:28:01','',1130,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-Swaychic.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1136,2,'2015-11-19 16:55:58','2015-11-19 15:55:58','','email-segmentation-case-studies-cover','','inherit','open','closed','','email-segmentation-case-studies-cover','','','2015-11-19 16:56:29','2015-11-19 15:56:29','',1130,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-cover.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1137,2,'2015-11-19 17:00:09','2015-11-19 16:00:09','','5-killer-email-segmentation-case-studies-cover','','inherit','open','closed','','5-killer-email-segmentation-case-studies-cover','','','2015-11-19 17:00:25','2015-11-19 16:00:25','',1130,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/5-killer-email-segmentation-case-studies-cover.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1140,3,'2015-11-23 18:50:50','2015-11-23 17:50:50','Email still matters. A lot! In some previous posts we went through the <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/why-email-marketing-segmentation-matters\">benefits of email marketing</a> and some real working <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/5-killer-email-segmentation-case-studies\">case studies of email marketing segmentation strategies</a> that have proven results.\r\n\r\nEmail marketing has some major advantages compared to most other marketing channels. It\'s got high reach, it\'s low cost and it\'s easy to test once you\'ve built a small email list.\r\n\r\nIn this post we’re going to cover the top three types of email marketing strategies, how to employ them successfully, and finally their advantages and disadvantages.\r\n<h3>1. Educational Emails</h3>\r\nEducational emails revolve around providing your subscribers with industry knowledge that\'s connected to your business or product.\r\n\r\nThis involves creating a piece of content (e.g. infographic, white papers, blog articles) and giving your subscribers a snippet of the content in an email prompting them back to your website. Or if your message is concise you may just send an email.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1160\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/educational_email.jpg\" alt=\"an educational email sent by help scout as part of their email marketing strategy\" width=\"680\" height=\"468\" />\r\n\r\nEducational content and email is really effective if your target audience is facing a problem or issue that your company can solve.\r\n\r\n<strong>Advantages</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>It builds trust</strong>. As you continually provide your subscribers with valuable information you will be seen as a industry thought leader. This increases they likely-hood they will evaluate your product when looking to purchase.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>It\'s sharable</strong>. As you create and deliver more valuable information your subscribers will be more likely to spread it on social networks. The more your content get shared the more leads you\'ll generate.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>It drives sales</strong>. If you consistently send the right information, at the right time, as your subscriber moves through the<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/why-email-marketing-segmentation-matters\" target=\"_blank\"> sales cycle</a> you increase the likely-hood that they will purchase from you over a competitor.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Disadvantages</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>It takes time</strong>. When you send an educational email, you’re trying to build a relationship with your customers. With that in mind it can take time to create relevant content and emails.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>2. Promotional Emails</h3>\r\nNothing entices a customer more than a great deal. Your customer saves a few bucks and your revenue gets a boost. Not bad, right?\r\n\r\nMost e-commerce businesses rely heavily on promotional emails. But regardless of what kind of a business you run, you should know how to make offers in your emails.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1161\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/promotional_email.jpg\" alt=\"A promotional email sent as part of an email marketing strategy\" width=\"662\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\nPromotional emails aren’t reserved for only things like, “Get 70% off today only!” A promotional email can offer other perks too, like free shipping or a free product trial.\r\n\r\n<strong>Advantages</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Easy to set up</strong>. Once you know what it is you’re promoting, all you need is the copy. Dedicated emails don’t have to rely on graphics or fancy layouts to engage readers.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Easy to track</strong>. As promotional emails tend to have only one call-to-action it\'s easy to see who clicked through and purchased.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Quick impact on sales</strong>. If you\'re not hitting your targets for the month you can run a quick promotion to boost sales.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Disadvantages</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Limited in what you can include</strong>. The whole point on promotional emails is having one very clear call-to-action. Your message will become quickly diluted if you start including multiple offers etc.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Can be irrelevant to subscriber</strong>. Some people on your email marketing list won\'t get any value from your promotion and may unsubscribe. This may happen if you carry a big product range and send a Male a \"70% off womens jeans\" promotion. To keep them relevant you need to segment your list.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>3. Lead Nurturing Emails</h3>\r\nFor many businesses, building a relationship with their leads is the primary reason for sending any emails. This is because you can specifically targeting subscribers that you want to turn into customers. This can be time consuming to set up but can yield massive returns.\r\n\r\nPeople do business with businesses they know and trust. The first time someone converts on your website, the likelihood that they really know who you are or understand why they should do business with you is pretty slim. As you build relationships with your leads you are increasing the chances that they will purchase from you as they move through the sales cycle.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1162\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/lead_nurturing_email.jpg\" alt=\"lead nurturing email example by hubspot as part of their email marketing strategy\" width=\"800\" height=\"590\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Example of an automated lead nurturing email by HubSpot</em></p>\r\nIt is important to note that relationship building should be part of each email marketing strategy. No matter what kind of an email you send.\r\n\r\n<strong>Advantages</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Can be very personable</strong>. You are connecting directly with the client and tailoring your email and pitch specifically to them. This in turn will increase brand awareness and build trust.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Increase response</strong> <strong>rate</strong>. According to HubSpot, lead nurturing emails achieve <a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/29757/Lead-Nurturing-Generates-Nearly-3X-More-Clicks-Than-Email-Blasts-Data.aspx\">4-10 times the response rate</a> compared to standalone emails.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Shorten sales cycle</strong>.  <a title=\"Market2Lead found\" href=\"http://customerexperiencematrix.blogspot.com/2010/09/hard-data-to-justify-your-marketing.html\" target=\"_self\">Market2Lead found </a>that nurtured leads have a 23% shorter sales cycle.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Disadvantages</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Time consuming</strong>. The main disadvantage is probably the amount of time and effort you’ll need to put behind your lead nurturing campaigns. Chances are each client will need a slightly tweaked approach, meaning very little can be templated.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>They generate less buzz.</strong> More lead nurturing emails are only sent to one address, rather than the thousands-strong subscriber list of your newsletter.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Takeaways</h3>\r\nThere we have it! Three of the top email marketing strategies you should be implementing if you\'re taking email marketing seriously.\r\n\r\nGenerally speaking, the most effective email marketing campaign is  a mix of all of these techniques. Typically you should use three different email marketing strategies. You can emphasize some more than others, but you shouldn’t just stubbornly stick to one strategy.\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>\r\n&nbsp;','3 highly effective email marketing strategies','','publish','open','open','','3-highly-effective-email-marketing-strategies','','','2015-11-24 11:36:42','2015-11-24 10:36:42','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1140',0,'post','',0),(1143,4,'2015-11-20 13:13:23','2015-11-20 12:13:23','','Generate Zapier Key In Birdleaf','Click \'Generate Key\' to get your unique Zapier key.','inherit','open','closed','','generate-key','','','2015-11-20 13:13:59','2015-11-20 12:13:59','',1125,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Generate-Key.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1145,4,'2015-11-20 13:21:39','2015-11-20 12:21:39','','Copy Your Zapier Key','','inherit','open','closed','','copy-your-zapier-key-2','','','2015-11-20 13:21:57','2015-11-20 12:21:57','',1125,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Copy-Your-Zapier-Key1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1146,4,'2015-11-20 15:00:15','2015-11-20 14:00:15','We recently launched our first 3rd party integration - <a href=\"https://zapier.com\" target=\"_blank\">Zapier</a>! Using Zapier, you can connect Birdleaf to over 500 other services to automatically add emails to and export data from Birdleaf. A common request has been to automatically add new MailChimp signups to a list in Birdleaf.\r\n\r\nAll this is now possible, and can be set up in just a few minutes! Before getting started, there are some quick necessary steps like getting your Zapier key which are <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/how-to-use-zapier-with-birdleaf\" target=\"_blank\">covered in a previous post</a>, so check that out before going any further here :)\r\n\r\nRight, let\'s get to it...\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Sign in to your Zapier account, or click <a href=\"http://bit.ly/blzapinvt\" target=\"_blank\">this link</a> if you haven\'t accepted an invite to add Birdleaf to Zapier yet.</li>\r\n	<li>Click \'Make a Zap\' on the right of the dashboard area.<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1150\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-20-at-3.11.20-p.m.-930x255.png\" alt=\"Make a Zap\" width=\"930\" height=\"255\" /></li>\r\n	<li>Click \'Choose a Trigger App\' and select MailChimp.</li>\r\n	<li>Click \'Choose a Trigger\' and select \'New Subscriber\'.</li>\r\n	<li>From \'Choose an Action App\' select Birdleaf.</li>\r\n	<li>Then click \'Choose an Action\' and select \'Add Email Address\'. Your setup should look like this so far - <img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1151\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Inital-Connect-Birdleaf-Mailchimp-930x216.png\" alt=\"Inital Connect Birdleaf Mailchimp\" width=\"930\" height=\"216\" /></li>\r\n	<li>Click \'Choose a Mailchimp Account\'. Select an existing Mailchimp account from the dropdown menu, or connect a new one. There\'s a help article for this <a href=\"https://zapier.com/help/mailchimp/#get-started-mailchimp\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> if you need a hand.</li>\r\n	<li>Click \'Choose a Birdleaf Account\'. If you already have a Birdleaf account linked, choose that account, or you can connect a new Birdleaf account. To connect an account, in the pop up box first name your Birdleaf account. Then, under \'API Key\' enter the Zapier key given to you in your Birdleaf <a href=\"http://app.birdleaf.io/#/user/account\" target=\"_blank\">Account</a> page. If you need help getting your key, <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/how-to-use-zapier-with-birdleaf\" target=\"_blank\">see here</a>.<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1152\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-20-at-3.36.58-p.m.-930x332.png\" alt=\"Linking Your Birdleaf Account In Zapier\" width=\"930\" height=\"332\" /></li>\r\n	<li>Nearly there! Under \'Filter Mailchimp Triggers\', select the list in your Mailchimp account which you would like emails to be added from. In the picture below we\'ve chosen our \'Newsletter Subscribers\' list, so any emails added to that list (when someone signs up to our newsletter) will be sent to Birdleaf.<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-20-at-3.48.50-p.m..png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1153\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-20-at-3.48.50-p.m.-930x365.png\" alt=\"Choose a MailChimp list\" width=\"930\" height=\"365\" /></a>We also only want to send subscribers that we get an email for. This is likely to be pretty much every subscriber, but you can optionally add a \'Custom Filter\' to make sure only ones with emails are sent (see above picture).</li>\r\n	<li>Now we need to tell Birdleaf what to do with the info from MailChimp. Select the list in Birdleaf where you would like your MailChimp subscribers to be added. You also need to let Birdleaf know which MailChimp field is the email address, so we know what to look up! Under \'Email\' click \'Insert Fields\', the select \'Email\'.<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1154\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-20-at-3.53.58-p.m.-930x270.png\" alt=\"Match MailChimp to Birdleaf in Zapier\" width=\"930\" height=\"270\" /></li>\r\n	<li>Before finishing you can optionally test your connection to make sure everything is working.</li>\r\n	<li>Finally, give your Zap a name and turn it on! <img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1155\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-20-at-4.02.01-p.m.-930x199.png\" alt=\"Name Your MailChimp To Birdleaf Zap\" width=\"930\" height=\"199\" />Once it\'s turned on, new subscribers to that MailChimp list will automatically be added to your Birdleaf account and researched!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nI hope this helps! If you have any questions please leave a comment below, <a href=\"mailto:support@birdleaf.io\">email us</a>, or contact us through the in-app support chat :)\r\n<h2></h2>','Connecting Birdleaf To MailChimp Using Zapier','','publish','open','open','','connecting-birdleaf-to-mailchimp-using-zapier','','','2015-11-24 11:14:12','2015-11-24 10:14:12','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1146',0,'post','',0),(1147,4,'2015-11-20 15:35:14','2015-11-20 14:35:14','','zapier-logo','','inherit','open','closed','','zapier-logo','','','2015-11-20 15:35:14','2015-11-20 14:35:14','',1125,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/zapier-l