,'2015-11-20 17:02:22','2015-11-20 16:02:22','','Name Your MailChimp To Birdleaf Zap','','inherit','open','closed','','screen-shot-2015-11-20-at-4-02-01-p-m','','','2015-11-20 17:02:38','2015-11-20 16:02:38','',1146,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-20-at-4.02.01-p.m..png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1156,3,'2015-11-23 11:49:34','2015-11-23 10:49:34','','zapier+birdleaf','','inherit','open','closed','','zapierbirdleaf','','','2015-11-23 11:49:34','2015-11-23 10:49:34','',1125,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/zapier-birdleaf.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1158,3,'2015-11-23 13:04:16','2015-11-23 12:04:16','','mailchimp+birdleaf','','inherit','open','closed','','mailchimpbirdleaf','','','2015-11-23 13:04:16','2015-11-23 12:04:16','',1146,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/mailchimp-birdleaf.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1160,3,'2015-11-24 10:35:28','2015-11-24 09:35:28','an educational email sent by help scout','educational_email','','inherit','open','closed','','educational_email','','','2015-11-24 10:36:26','2015-11-24 09:36:26','',1140,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/educational_email.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1161,3,'2015-11-24 10:38:38','2015-11-24 09:38:38','','promotional_email','','inherit','open','closed','','promotional_email','','','2015-11-24 10:40:07','2015-11-24 09:40:07','',1140,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/promotional_email.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1162,3,'2015-11-24 10:43:31','2015-11-24 09:43:31','','lead_nurturing_email','','inherit','open','closed','','lead_nurturing_email','','','2015-11-24 10:44:04','2015-11-24 09:44:04','',1140,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/lead_nurturing_email.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1163,3,'2015-11-24 11:02:21','2015-11-24 10:02:21','','email_marketing_strategies_cover','','inherit','open','closed','','email_marketing_strategies_cover','','','2015-11-24 11:02:46','2015-11-24 10:02:46','',1140,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email_marketing_strategies_cover.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1164,3,'2015-11-25 21:22:27','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Importance of demographical segmentation for email marketing','','draft','open','open','','importance-of-demographical-segmentation-for-email-marketing','','','2015-11-25 21:22:27','2015-11-25 20:22:27','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1164',0,'post','',0),(1166,3,'2015-11-25 09:24:23','2015-11-25 08:24:23','All this talk and debate about emails death is greatly exaggerated. A recent study concluded that email is almost 40 times better at acquiring new customers than Facebook, Twitter and Google Adwords.\r\n\r\nWith that in mind, email marketing should play a heavy role in your overall marketing strategy! In this post we\'ll look at some of the best email marketing and newsletter apps to help you kick start your email marketing.\r\n\r\nAll the email marketing apps we mention are capable of sending great newsletters. A lot of the apps are a lot more feature rich than others so it depends what <a href=\"https://emailexperience.org/2014/12/the-5-stages-of-email-segmentation-sophistication-how-evolved-are-you/\" target=\"_blank\">approach</a> you want to take with your email marketing.\r\n<h3>Factors to consider</h3>\r\nWhen deciding on which email marketing app you should be purchase to run your campaigns there are 5 key factors to consider. Some factors will be more important than others depending on your business but it is worth keeping the importance of each factor to your business in mind as you read through this post.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Price</li>\r\n	<li>Reporting &amp; Analytics</li>\r\n	<li>Segmentation</li>\r\n	<li>Customization</li>\r\n	<li>Automation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBelow are the best apps that send email newsletters (<em>in no particular order</em>). For each app you\'ll find a screenshot, a brief review, and pricing information.\r\n<h3>1. Mailchimp</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1167\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Mailchimp_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of mailchimps email designer\" width=\"800\" height=\"454\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://mailchimp.com\" target=\"_blank\">Mailchimp</a> is one of the most popular email marketing apps. It is incredibly simple and intuitive to use and it has tonnes of really slick pre-designed templates.  MailChimp offers everything from a drag-and-drop email editor to detailed subscriber profiles that track your contacts interactions with your emails, and more.\r\n\r\nMailChimp allows you to easily customize your email campaigns for recipients with merge-tags. If you want to grab your reader’s attention by including their first name in the subject line (<a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/psychology-personalization\" target=\"_blank\">personalization is proven to be an effective marketing tactic</a>), simple add the merge tag *|FNAME|*to the subject line. MailChimp also offers really simple segmentation. You can set certain criteria a subscriber must meet before sending them a tailored message. For example, for every subscriber whose location is New York send them the \"New York Flash Sale\" email.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://mailchimp.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> MailChimp offer a free plan that allows allows you have up to 2,000 subscribers and 12,000 emails per month. From there they charge based on usage starting at $10 per month for unlimited emails to 500 subscribers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>2. AWeber</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1168\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/AWeber_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of awebers email designer\" width=\"800\" height=\"458\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.aweber.com\" target=\"_blank\">AWeber</a> is another great option for those that are new to email marketing. All you need to do is simply choose a template (mobile responsive) and input your content. So no faffing about with design. However, for anyone who wants to customize the emails they send to their customers, this might not be their preferred way of working. There are a huge amount of templates to choose from <em>(over 700 in fact)</em> or you can pay a premium to have a template designed for you <em>(starting from $29)</em>.\r\n\r\nIf you want to really make the most of your campaigns and generate a high ROI, learning to manage your subscribers effectively is essential. AWeber allows you to do a really good job at this. You can create heavily customized submission forms with up to 25 fields. Using this data it is really simple to segment your subscribers into different groups ensuring you provide more personalized content for the reader.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.aweber.com/pricing\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> AWeber offers a free fully functional 30-day trial. After this prices start at $19 per month for up to 500 subscribers and unlimited emails.\r\n<h3>3. ActiveCampaign</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1170\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ActiveCampaign_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of ActiveCampaigns dashboard\" width=\"800\" height=\"459\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.activecampaign.com\" target=\"_blank\">ActiveCampaign</a> has one of the most comprehensive offerings on this list. Their product combines a full CRM and marketing automation suite along with its email newsletter tool meaning it’s not just about emails. It is really a platform to allow you to grow your business, manage your leads and your clients too.\r\n\r\nActiveCampaign provides a simple tool to create customized sign-up forms that you can display on your website and Facebook page to help you build your subscriber list. For your emails you have a full-featured email editor. You can drag-and-drop email elements, design them the way you want, and quickly send your finished newsletters off to your subscribers.\r\n\r\nThe best bit of ActiveCampaign is its campaign automation. They offer a variety of tools you can use to target your customers with timely messages and personalized content without spending every waking hour managing your campaigns.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.activecampaign.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> ActiveCampaign offer a 14-day trial. After this the entry level package is $9 per month for up to 500 subscribers and unlimited emails.\r\n<h3>4. GetResponse</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1171\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/GetResponse_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of Get Response email designer\" width=\"800\" height=\"457\" />\r\n\r\nWith over <a href=\"https://litmus.com/blog/53-of-emails-opened-on-mobile-outlook-opens-decrease-33\" target=\"_blank\">53% of emails</a> opened on mobile, <a href=\"http://www.getresponse.com\" target=\"_blank\">GetResponse</a> is a great option for those that put mobile first. It\'s biggest strength is its responsive email design functionality that automatically adjusts your newsletter\'s template so if a user is reading it on a smartphone, the layout and fonts will be automatically optimised for it. A lot of the competing platforms have added this functionality recently, but GetResponse is one of the only services that offers live mobile-previews.\r\n\r\nGetResponse offers one of the most comprehensive reporting and analytics tools. Aside from the basics of open rates and clickthroughs they offer \'one click segmentation\' and \'email ROI\' to name a few, meaning tracking important metrics for your business is a breeze. One other cool feature that GetResponse offers is a landing page creator to collect more leads.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://secure.getresponse.com/pricing/en/\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> GetResponse offer a free 30-day trial. After this pricing starts at $15 for up to 1000 contacts and unlimited emails.\r\n<h3>5. Constant Contact</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1172\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/constantcontact_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of ConstantContact email designer\" width=\"800\" height=\"458\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.constantcontact.com\" target=\"_blank\">ConstantContact</a> offer a really slick drag and drop editor making it really seamless to customize one of their templates. They also offer a lot of extras that you can include in your emails such as polls, surveys, videos and more.\r\n\r\nYou can create comprehensive reports on your email campaigns to show number of opt-outs, complaints, bounces, forwards and click-throughs. The social-share tool allows you to easily post and track your emails on all your social networks. The social stats reporting tools clearly illustrate the number of shares, likes, tweets and more that your messages receive. You can also see the number of total social shares and page views your email campaign has generated.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.constantcontact.com/pricing\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> ConstantContact offer a 60-day free trial. After  this plans start at $20 per month for up to 500 subscribers and unlimited emails.\r\n<h3>6. TinyLetter</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1173\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/tinyletter_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of TinyLetter email designer\" width=\"800\" height=\"458\" /></h3>\r\nIf you\'re looking for a no frills and super basic app then TinyLetter is for you! It\'s ridiculously simple to use and has pretty much no features. It simply lets you create simple plain-text  newsletters and basic custom landing pages allowing you to collect email addresses.\r\n\r\nTinyLetter is run by MailChimp and they will only allow you add up to 5,000 subscribers. After that you\'ll need a more feature rich platform like MailChimp.\r\n\r\nPricing: Absolutely Free!\r\n<h3>7. Emma</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1174\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Emma_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of Emma email designer\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" /></h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://myemma.com\" target=\"_blank\">Emma</a>\'s email app is well known for its simplicity and killer design. They provide you with a really slick drag and drop email editor and a lot of nice templates. One really interesting thing about Emma is they offer a concierge service to design and write your emails for you as well as setting up drip campaigns. So if you were looking on hiring a designer to craft your email campaigns then you should look no further than Emma as they know what works for each use case.\r\n\r\nThe also offer smart audience segmentation with unlimited groups and contact fields and simple automation workflows that keep your subscribers engaged.\r\n\r\nPricing: Emma offer a 30-day free-trial after which pricing starts at $49 per month for up to 2,500 subscribers and unlimited emails.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>8. Mailjet</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1175\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/mailjet_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of Mailjets email designer\" width=\"800\" height=\"449\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://mailjet.com\" target=\"_blank\">Mailjet</a> allows you to send marketing and transactional email from one account to optimize your customer’s email experience. In addition to their send API, Mailjet includes a simple template designer where you can design responsive emails  templates on the fly without the help of your developer.\r\n\r\nThe big selling point for Mailjet is its powerful list segmentation where you can segment your subscribers based on preferences, behaviours and characteristics. Their  send API can be leveraged to constantly push fresh contact data from any source meaning the segmentation possibilities are endless!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.mailjet.com/pricing_v3\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> Mailjet offer a free 30-day trial and plans start from $7.49 per month for 30,000 emails.\r\n<h3>9. Campaign Monitor</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1176\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CampaignMonitor_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of Campaign Monitors email designer\" width=\"800\" height=\"456\" />\r\n<p class=\"p1\">While using templates for your email marketing has many benefits, they can start to look a bit generic and have less impact. <a href=\"https://www.campaignmonitor.com\" target=\"_blank\">Campaign Monitor</a> combats this by making it as easy as possible to code your own templates. You can import your own HTML templates by using Campaign Monitor’s tags to make sure you’re able to use its integrated template editor to edit and personalize content in future. That being said they do offer some nice templates that you can use and customize off the bat.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Campaign Monitor generates actual screens of your email design in popular email clients like Gmail, Hotmail, Yahoo and many more. This allows you to get your campaigns displaying properly in all email clients.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><a href=\"https://www.campaignmonitor.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing: </a>Campaign Monitor have a free trial, but you can\'t send any emails. Pricing starts at $9 per month for up to 500 contacts and 2,500 emails.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>10. Freshmail</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1177\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/freshmail_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of Freshmail email designer\" width=\"800\" height=\"460\" /></h3>\r\nWhen you go to build your first newsletter in <a href=\"http://freshmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">FreshMail</a> the most noticable thing is the amount of customization you have. The FreshMail Designer is drag and drop and they offer very slick ready-to-use email templates. They offer a hugh amount of graphics so you can play around with lots of different designs.\r\n\r\nOne thing that is very notable from their editor is the ability to create emails that look like really nice product demo pages. Ideal for product launches and announcements. On top of their editor the offer good analytics and drip campaigns.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://freshmail.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\">Pricing:</a> FreshMail offer a free account for up to 500 subscribers and unlimted emails. Pricing then starts at $15 per month for up to 1000 subscribers.\r\n<h3>Takeaways</h3>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">And there we have it, that concludes our list of the 10 best email marketing and newsletter apps! From ridiculously simple email marketing apps to full-blown marketing automation apps there should be at least one that fits the bill for your business!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Pretty much all of the apps on the list offer a free trial allowing you to get a good overview of the product by creating an email campaign. Even if you only send a test one to your own email address.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>','The 10 best email marketing and newsletter apps','','publish','open','open','','the-10-best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-25 21:23:15','2015-11-25 20:23:15','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1166',0,'post','',0),(1167,3,'2015-11-24 22:21:29','2015-11-24 21:21:29','','Mailchimp_best email marketing and newsletter apps','','inherit','open','closed','','mailchimp_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-24 22:22:11','2015-11-24 21:22:11','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Mailchimp_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1168,3,'2015-11-24 22:24:24','2015-11-24 21:24:24','','AWeber_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','inherit','open','closed','','aweber_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-24 22:24:52','2015-11-24 21:24:52','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/AWeber_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1170,3,'2015-11-24 22:30:46','2015-11-24 21:30:46','','ActiveCampaign_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','inherit','open','closed','','activecampaign_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-24 22:31:28','2015-11-24 21:31:28','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ActiveCampaign_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1171,3,'2015-11-24 22:40:14','2015-11-24 21:40:14','','GetResponse_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','inherit','open','closed','','getresponse_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-24 22:40:56','2015-11-24 21:40:56','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/GetResponse_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1172,3,'2015-11-24 22:53:14','2015-11-24 21:53:14','','constantcontact_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','inherit','open','closed','','constantcontact_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-24 22:53:50','2015-11-24 21:53:50','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/constantcontact_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1173,3,'2015-11-24 23:00:45','2015-11-24 22:00:45','','tinyletter_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','inherit','open','closed','','tinyletter_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-24 23:01:08','2015-11-24 22:01:08','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/tinyletter_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1174,3,'2015-11-24 23:02:40','2015-11-24 22:02:40','','Emma_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','inherit','open','closed','','emma_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-24 23:02:59','2015-11-24 22:02:59','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Emma_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1175,3,'2015-11-24 23:04:35','2015-11-24 22:04:35','','mailjet_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','inherit','open','closed','','mailjet_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-24 23:04:55','2015-11-24 22:04:55','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/mailjet_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1176,3,'2015-11-24 23:07:08','2015-11-24 22:07:08','','CampaignMonitor_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','inherit','open','closed','','campaignmonitor_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-24 23:07:31','2015-11-24 22:07:31','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CampaignMonitor_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1177,3,'2015-11-24 23:08:52','2015-11-24 22:08:52','','freshmail_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','inherit','open','closed','','freshmail_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps','','','2015-11-24 23:09:18','2015-11-24 22:09:18','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/freshmail_best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1179,3,'2015-11-25 13:11:51','2015-11-25 12:11:51','','10 best email marketing and newsletter apps','','inherit','open','closed','','10-best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps-cover-image','','','2015-11-25 13:12:29','2015-11-25 12:12:29','',1166,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/10-best-email-marketing-and-newsletter-apps-cover-image.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1181,3,'2015-11-27 14:32:25','2015-11-27 14:32:25','In terms of users,  email out numbers any social network. By the end of 2016 there will be over 4.3 billion email accounts. In addition to this, email marketing is still ranked as the best channel in terms of return on investment.\r\n\r\nBut is your email marketing performing as well as it could? A report published by <a href=\"https://www.marketingsherpa.com/data/public/reports/benchmark-reports/EXCERPT-BMR-2013-Email-Marketing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Marketing Sherpa</a> found that 83% of marketers surveyed are overlooking the importance of tracking and testing their email marketing and metrics.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1192\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-stats.jpg\" alt=\"Stats for marketers that are using email marketing optimization tactics\" width=\"300\" height=\"304\" />\r\n\r\nIn this post I\'ll give you 10 actionable email marketing optimization tactics you can use to keep your subscribers subscribed and interested in your emails.\r\n<h3>1. Optimize for mobile</h3>\r\nSmartphones and tablets can no longer be ignored by email marketers. <a href=\"https://litmus.com/blog/53-of-emails-opened-on-mobile-outlook-opens-decrease-33\" target=\"_blank\">A report</a> published last year found that 53% of emails are opened on mobile. And that figure will continue to grow rapidly over the coming years.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1184\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-mobile-optimized.jpg\" alt=\"A mobile optimized email example\" width=\"352\" height=\"662\" />\r\n\r\nIf that statistic doesn\'t give food for thought, this will. <a href=\"http://www.bizreport.com/2013/03/bluehornet-302-unsubscribe-on-receipt-of-a-badly-formatted-m.html\" target=\"_blank\">A report </a>from email marketing company BlueHornet found that over 80% of consumers immediately delete emails that don\'t display properly on  a mobile device.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Takeaway: </strong></em>If you\'re not optimizing for mobile you have an 80% chance that message will be instantly deleted and run the risk of losing that subscriber altogether.\r\n<h3>2. Match your subject line to your email copy</h3>\r\nMost of your subscribers are probably being bombarded with spammy emails on a daily basis. The last thing they want to do is open an email with a compelling subject line only to find the body of the email has nothing to do with the subject.\r\n\r\nYour subject line offers a snippet of the email. If it is misleading you are likely to frustrate your readers and deter them from opening future emails.\r\n\r\nBusinesses who use misleading subject lines may see a lift in open rates, but will more than likely experience decreased click-through rates as the content doesn\'t match the promise of the subject.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Takeaway: </em></strong>Your subject line offers a promise of the email. To make sure the align you should write the subject line after you\'ve written the content.\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>3. Optimize landing pages to match email copy</h3>\r\nTo create a seamless online experience for your customers you need to create specific landing pages for specific email marketing campaigns.\r\n\r\nDoes the landing page fulfill the expectations of the value proposition of the link leading into it? If the answer is no, then the reader will likely be confused and you\'ll decrease the chances of converting that sale.\r\n\r\nASOS do an awesome job of this. I get this email:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1185\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-email.jpg\" alt=\"Example email from ASOS\" width=\"800\" height=\"500\" />\r\n\r\nAnd here\'s the corresponding landing page to that CTA:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-offer-landing-page.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1187\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-offer-landing-page.jpg\" alt=\"ASOS landing page that corresponds to email\" width=\"800\" height=\"656\" /></a>\r\n\r\nI love the way that the CTA is tied to the landing page. All I have to do is pick the size and checkout. Two simple steps.\r\n\r\nThe email is essentially a template for your website. If I get a promotional email for \"50% off shoes\" and the email directs me to a page with jumpers, the likelihood is I\'ll just close the tab.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Takeaway: </strong></em>Increase your sales conversions by matching your email campaigns with your landing pages.\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>4. Include social sharing</h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.getresponse.com/social-sharing-boosts-email-ctr.html\" target=\"_blank\">GetResponse </a>report that emails including social sharing buttons have a 158% higher click-through rate than those that don\'t.\r\n\r\nBy including social sharing buttons in your emails you create a simple way for your subscribers to share with their social following. This in turn could generate new leads for your business.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1188 size-full\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-social-share.jpg\" alt=\"Email from groove that includes a social share button\" width=\"800\" height=\"448\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Takeaway: </em></strong>Include social share buttons in your emails you\'ll extend your email reach.\r\n<h3>5. Optimize your emails with images turned off</h3>\r\nThis is a really simple but effective tip that will improve click-through rates from your emails. A lot of email providers, like Outlook &amp; Yahoo, have images turned off by default which can have a disastrous effect on your email campaigns.\r\n\r\nObviously using images in your email campaigns allows you to create much nicer and compelling emails, so I\'m not saying you shouldn\'t use images. Just get smart about the design/layout. At the very least you should be placing useful and descriptive alt tags on all your images, as this text will display instead if the images don\'t display.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1189\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-non-image-optimized.jpg\" alt=\"example email optimized for when images don\'t display\" width=\"800\" height=\"552\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>When image appears vs when they don\'t</em></p>\r\nCheck out <a href=\"https://litmus.com/blog/pizzaexpress-inspires-with-images-off-email-optimization\" target=\"_blank\">this example</a> of how PizzaExpress optimize their emails in the event that the images don\'t show.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Takeaway: </strong></em>Make sure to include descriptive alt tags for your images so the reader can understand the email if the images don\'t display.\r\n<h3>6. Segment your subscribers</h3>\r\nRelevance is central to today’s marketing strategy, and buyers have come to expect personalization in their communications. Four out of ten subscribers will mark an email as spam simply because they were irrelevant.\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Emails that have been tailored to specific audiences through segmentation get 39% more opens and 24% more revenue than non-segmented lists.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">You can build your segmentation strategy based on your different customer personas. Once you\'ve defined your different segments you can identify the data points you wish to use to divide your list and then begin crafting tailored content.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><em><strong>Takeaway: </strong></em>Tailor your campaigns to each segment and you\'ll increase click-through rates and profits.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Create a clear CTA</h3>\r\nOne of the best ways to increase conversion rates is to optimize your call-to-action buttons. The purpose of your CTA is to leave no room for doubt\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1190\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-clear-cta.jpg\" alt=\"Example of an email with one clear CTA\" width=\"800\" height=\"618\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Good example of an email with a clear CTA</em></p>\r\nThe best performing emails will contain one clear CTA.\r\n\r\nYour call to action should be obvious and visually appealing, leaving no room for doubt about what the reader should do next.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Takeaway: </strong></em>Include one clear and prominent CTA to increase your click-through rates.\r\n<h3>8. Use a newsletter service</h3>\r\nThis probably seems like a weird point but it is really important that you use the right email marketing provider. When running email marketing campaigns a lot of businesses don\'t think about the deliverability of their emails.\r\n\r\nSome service providers have much better deliverability rates than others. <a href=\"http://www.quicksprout.com/2013/06/24/5-simple-ways-to-increase-your-email-deliverability-rates/\" target=\"_blank\">Quicksprout</a> found that switching provider resulted in a 44% increase in open rates and a 67% increase in click-through rates. The email copy and subject lines were the exact same on both services.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Takeaway: </em></strong>Do research before picking an email marketing app.\r\n<h3>9. Personalize you emails</h3>\r\nEmail is one of the most personal mediums we have to communicate with our customers at scale. Subscribers understand that email campaigns are sent out to the masses, but that doesn\'t mean they will settle for generic email blasts.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1191\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-personalization-fail.jpg\" alt=\"A email attempting to be personal but put the wrong tag where name should be\" width=\"800\" height=\"550\" />\r\n\r\nWhen a subscriber signs up and uses your product try and get as much information as possible. This will allow you to include personalizations such as name, interests, location and so on.\r\n\r\nAlso writing in the second person is a lot more personable, so try and use language like \'you\' and \'me\'.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Takeaway: </strong></em>Personalizing your emails will create a much better tone in your emails and will build better relationships with your subscribers.\r\n<h3>10. Make your emails as short as possible</h3>\r\nThe shorter the email, the greater the chance someone will read and engage with them. Most people suffer from email overload. As a result they will give your email a quick scan and decide within a few seconds whether to delete it or click-through. Unnecessarily long emails introduce friction and decrease the chances the reader will interact with the email.\r\n\r\nFor newsletters in particular, you should just include a short teaser enticing the reader to click through to the full content on your website.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Takeaway: </em></strong>To increase the chances of your readers clicking through shorten your emails and reduce the amount of text.\r\n\r\nAnd there you have it. We\'ve just gone through 10 email marketing optimization tactics you can start incorporating into your email marketing straight away and increase your ROI.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>','10 email marketing optimization tactics to boost revenue','','publish','open','open','','10-email-marketing-optimization-tactics-to-boost-revenue','','','2015-11-27 14:32:25','2015-11-27 14:32:25','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1181',0,'post','',0),(1184,2,'2015-11-27 11:07:04','2015-11-27 11:07:04','','Email marketing optimization tactics mobile optimized','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-optimization-tactics-mobile-optimized','','','2015-11-27 11:07:57','2015-11-27 11:07:57','',1181,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-mobile-optimized.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1185,2,'2015-11-27 11:26:32','2015-11-27 11:26:32','','Email marketing optimization tactics asos-email','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-email','','','2015-11-27 11:26:56','2015-11-27 11:26:56','',1181,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-email.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1186,2,'2015-11-27 11:30:16','2015-11-27 11:30:16','','Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-landing-page','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-landing-page','','','2015-11-27 11:31:13','2015-11-27 11:31:13','',1181,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-landing-page.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1187,2,'2015-11-27 11:36:07','2015-11-27 11:36:07','','Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-offer-landing-page','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-offer-landing-page','','','2015-11-27 11:36:18','2015-11-27 11:36:18','',1181,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-asos-offer-landing-page.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1188,2,'2015-11-27 11:49:52','2015-11-27 11:49:52','','Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-social-share','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-optimization-tactics-social-share','','','2015-11-27 11:50:20','2015-11-27 11:50:20','',1181,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-social-share.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1189,2,'2015-11-27 11:58:20','2015-11-27 11:58:20','','Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-non-image-optimized','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-optimization-tactics-non-image-optimized','','','2015-11-27 11:58:44','2015-11-27 11:58:44','',1181,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-non-image-optimized.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1190,2,'2015-11-27 12:03:47','2015-11-27 12:03:47','','Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-clear-cta','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-optimization-tactics-clear-cta','','','2015-11-27 12:04:06','2015-11-27 12:04:06','',1181,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-clear-cta.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1191,2,'2015-11-27 12:10:33','2015-11-27 12:10:33','','Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-personalization-fail','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-optimization-tactics-personalization-fail','','','2015-11-27 12:11:24','2015-11-27 12:11:24','',1181,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-personalization-fail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1192,2,'2015-11-27 12:14:23','2015-11-27 12:14:23','','Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-stats','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-optimization-tactics-stats','','','2015-11-27 12:15:10','2015-11-27 12:15:10','',1181,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Email-marketing-optimization-tactics-stats.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1193,2,'2015-11-27 14:25:03','2015-11-27 14:25:03','','10-Actionable-Email-Marketing-Optimization-Tactics-cover','','inherit','open','closed','','10-actionable-email-marketing-optimization-tactics-cover','','','2015-11-27 14:25:03','2015-11-27 14:25:03','',1181,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/10-Actionable-Email-Marketing-Optimization-Tactics-cover.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1195,3,'2015-12-02 12:36:38','2015-12-02 12:36:38','Reports of email\'s death are greatly exaggerated. Marketers seem to be constantly changing their minds about email marketing and the returns it brings, yet all the email marketing statistics clearly claim that email marketing simply works and has a positive impact for business.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1199\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/email-marketing-statistics-google-email-is-dead.jpg\" alt=\"Google search results for &quot;email is dead&quot;\" width=\"800\" height=\"402\" />\r\n\r\nSo what is the current state of email marketing? Every month a new email-killing machine comes along, yet we\'re receiving more promotional emails than ever.\r\n\r\nIn this post we go through 20 of the top email marketing statistics that proves email marketing is still yielding massive returns, yet a lot of marketers are missing massive opportunities.\r\n<h3>Email Reach Statistics</h3>\r\nEmail out numbers any social network in terms of active users. By the end of 2016 there will be over 4.6 billion email accounts.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1201\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/email-marketing-statistics-reach.jpg\" alt=\"Email marketing statistics showing the amount of people who use email world wide\" width=\"800\" height=\"376\" />\r\n<strong>1.</strong> There are currently 4.4 billion email accounts. This is almost 3X more than twitter and facebook combined. (<a href=\"http://www.radicati.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Email-Statistics-Report-2015-2019-Executive-Summary.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Radicati Group</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>2.</strong> As of 2015 there are 2.6 billion active email users. Of these, 1.4 billion are accessing email on mobile devices. (<a href=\"http://www.radicati.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Email-Statistics-Report-2015-2019-Executive-Summary.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Radicati Group</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>3.</strong> It is estimated that in 2015 205.6 billion emails were sent and received each day. About 112.5 billion of those are for the business sector. (<a href=\"http://www.radicati.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Email-Statistics-Report-2015-2019-Executive-Summary.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Radicati Group</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>4.</strong> 78% of marketing emails are sent to personal email accounts. (<a href=\"http://www.bluekangaroo.com/media/ChoozOn-Blue_Kangaroo_Survey_on_Marketing_Emails_August_2012.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Blue Kangaroo</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>5.</strong> In 2015, the number of business emails sent and received totals 122 emails per user per day. Typically receiving 88 emails and sending 34 emails. (<a href=\"http://www.radicati.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Email-Statistics-Report-2015-2019-Executive-Summary.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Radicati Group</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>6.</strong> It is estimated that $2.4 billion was to be spent on email marketing in 2015. (<a href=\"https://www.cmocouncil.org/facts-stats-categories.php?view=all&amp;category=marketing-spend\" target=\"_blank\">CMO Council</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.</strong> There are currently 93% of marketers using email marketing. (<a href=\"http://go.webmarketing123.com/2015-State-of-Digital-Marketing-HP.html\" target=\"_blank\">Webmarketing 123</a>)\r\n<h3>Email Usage Statistics</h3>\r\nEmail is one of the most personal mediums we have to communicate with our customers at scale. But to be really effective at email marketing you need to understand their preferences.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1202\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/email-marketing-statistics-opening-environments.jpg\" alt=\"Email marketing statistics showing what environments emails are opened in. 53% open on mobile, 27% on desktop and 20% on webmail\" width=\"800\" height=\"425\" />\r\n<strong>8.</strong> 57% of subscribers spend 10-60 minutes a week browsing marketing emails. (<a href=\"http://www.bluekangaroo.com/media/ChoozOn-Blue_Kangaroo_Survey_on_Marketing_Emails_August_2012.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Blue Kangaroo</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>9.</strong> Mobile matters: as of 2015, 53% of emails are opened on mobile. (<a href=\"https://litmus.com/blog/53-of-emails-opened-on-mobile-outlook-opens-decrease-33\" target=\"_blank\">Litmus</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>10.</strong> Even though half of all emails are opened on mobile, only 42% of marketers are optimizing for mobile. (<a href=\"http://www.marketingsherpa.com/article/excerpt/free-excerpt-email-marketing-benchmark-2013\" target=\"_blank\">MarketingSherpa</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>11.</strong> 80% of consumers will immediately delete if they don\'t display properly. (<a href=\"http://www.bizreport.com/2013/03/bluehornet-302-unsubscribe-on-receipt-of-a-badly-formatted-m.html\" target=\"_blank\">BlueHornet</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>12.</strong> 91% of consumers check their email at least once a day. (<a href=\"https://expresspigeon.com/blog/2014/01/06/email-marketing-statistics-2014/\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressPigeon</a>)\r\n<h3>Email Effectiveness Statistics</h3>\r\nStill unsure if email is an effective channel for marketing? The statistics below speak for themselves.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1131 size-full\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/email-segmentation-case-studies-ROI-data.jpg\" alt=\"email segmentation case studies ROI data\" width=\"800\" height=\"368\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>New findings ROI has increased to $43 for every $1 invested.</i></p>\r\n<strong>13.</strong> Email converts better than SEO, digital ads, and social media. For every $1 invested in email marketing the average return is $43. That\'s an ROI of 4300%. (<a href=\"https://litmus.com/blog/53-of-emails-opened-on-mobile-outlook-opens-decrease-33\" target=\"_blank\">Litmus</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>14.</strong> The average open rate (across all sectors &amp; company sizes) is 22.14% and the average click-through-rate (CTR) is 2.79%. (<a href=\"http://mailchimp.com/resources/research/email-marketing-benchmarks/\" target=\"_blank\">MailChimp</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>15.</strong> Marketers find that 2X higher open rates occur on mobile versus desktop. (<a href=\"http://marketingland.com/77-percent-of-us-want-to-get-marketing-messages-via-email-theres-no-close-second-place-study-says-9420\" target=\"_blank\">MarketingLand</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>16.</strong> Emails that include social sharing buttons have a higher CTR of 158% than those that don\'t include share links. (<a href=\"http://blog.getresponse.com/social-sharing-boosts-email-ctr.html\" target=\"_blank\">GetResponse</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>17.</strong> Segmentation is critical. Four out of ten email subscribers mark emails as spam because they find the email irrelevant. (<a href=\"http://www.marketingsherpa.com/heap/WisdomReport2011.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">MarketingSherpa</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>18.</strong> Deliverability is a big issue: 17% of all emails never see the inside of a recipient’s inbox. This is due to defunct emails and SPAM traps. (<a href=\"http://www.ibm.com\" target=\"_blank\">IBM</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>19.</strong> Only 17% of marketers track and analyze their email marketing efforts, yet 60% of marketers believe email marketing produces positive ROI. (<a href=\"https://www.marketingsherpa.com/data/public/reports/benchmark-reports/EXCERPT-BMR-2013-Email-Marketing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">MarkertingSherpa</a>)\r\n\r\n<strong>20.</strong> You are 6X more likely to get a click through from an email campaign than you are from a tweet. Maybe it\'s time to start taking email marketing a bit more seriously. (<a href=\"https://www.campaignmonitor.com/blog/email-marketing/2014/07/email-marketing-vs-social-media/\" target=\"_blank\">CampaingMonitor</a>)\r\n<h3>Takeaways</h3>\r\nEmail clearly still matters and it doesn\'t look like it\'s going anywhere anytime soon. However from looking at these email marketing statistics it is quite clear that a lot of marketers have really bad habits.\r\n\r\nIt is evident that mobile is being completely neglected. This is one of the biggest reasons email marketing under performs. Also deliverability remains to be a massive issue, with nearly 20% of emails getting lost in transit.\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>','20 statistics that prove email marketing is (Still) Not Dead','','publish','open','open','','20-statistics-that-prove-email-marketing-is-still-not-dead-in-2015','','','2015-12-03 16:10:53','2015-12-03 16:10:53','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1195',0,'post','',0),(1196,3,'2015-12-03 16:03:07','2015-12-03 16:03:07','Are you using email marketing? How is it performing for you? Are you getting the returns you were expecting? This infographic compiles some of the most interesting <a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/20-statistics-that-prove-email-marketing-is-still-not-dead-in-2015\" target=\"_blank\">email marketing statistics</a> from 2015 that you should be aware of.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1197\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/email_marketing_statistics_2015.jpg\" alt=\"Infographic containing email statistics from 2015\" width=\"800\" height=\"3679\" />\r\n<h3>Facts and Stats To Tweet</h3>\r\n<strong>1. </strong>There are currently 4.4 billion email accounts. View email marketing growth statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/434bp\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>2. </strong>There are 2.6 billion people actively using email. View email marketing growth statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/2Idkd\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt; </a>\r\n\r\n<strong>3. </strong>1.4 billion people use email on mobile devices. View email marketing growth statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/5TG13\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>4. </strong>205 billion emails are sent and received each day. View email marketing statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/e83sd\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>5. </strong>At work you typically receive 88 emails a day. View email marketing growth statistics 2015 infographic<a href=\"http://ctt.ec/Ji74q\" target=\"_blank\"> &gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>6.</strong> At work you typically send 34 emails a day. View email marketing statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/eebGi\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>7. </strong>Emails with social sharing increase CTR by 158%. View email marketing growth statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/_qFMa\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>8. </strong>53% of emails are opened on a mobile device. View email marketing statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/fPS9f\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>9. </strong>89% of emails are not optimized for mobile. View email marketing growth statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/rj5ee\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>10. </strong>40% of subscribers mark emails as spam due to irrelevancy. View email marketing statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/Zef0X\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>11.</strong> Email marketing spend in 2015 was $2.4 billion. View email marketing growth statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/cVj1w\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>12. </strong>For every $1 spent on email marketing the average ROI is $43. View email marketing statistics 2015 infographic <a href=\"http://ctt.ec/C7k_L\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;tweet&lt;&lt;</a>\r\n<h3>Sources</h3>\r\n<strong>1. <a href=\"http://www.radicati.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Email-Statistics-Report-2015-2019-Executive-Summary.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Radicati Group</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>2. <a href=\"http://blog.getresponse.com/social-sharing-boosts-email-ctr.html\" target=\"_blank\">GetResponse</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>3. <a href=\"http://www.marketingsherpa.com/heap/WisdomReport2011.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">MarketingSherpa</a></b>\r\n\r\n<strong>4. <a href=\"https://litmus.com/blog/53-of-emails-opened-on-mobile-outlook-opens-decrease-33\" target=\"_blank\">Litmus</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>5. <a href=\"https://www.cmocouncil.org/facts-stats-categories.php?view=all&amp;category=marketing-spend\" target=\"_blank\">CMO Council</a></strong>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>','[Infographic] Mind Blowing Email Marketing Statistics 2015','','publish','open','open','','infographic-mind-blowing-email-marketing-statistics-2015','','','2015-12-03 16:10:32','2015-12-03 16:10:32','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1196',0,'post','',0),(1197,2,'2015-12-02 19:19:55','2015-12-02 19:19:55','','email_marketing_statistics_2015','','inherit','open','closed','','email_marketing_statistics_2015','','','2015-12-02 19:20:22','2015-12-02 19:20:22','',1196,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/email_marketing_statistics_2015.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1199,3,'2015-12-03 10:59:16','2015-12-03 10:59:16','','email-marketing-statistics-google-email-is-dead','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-statistics-google-email-is-dead','','','2015-12-03 10:59:42','2015-12-03 10:59:42','',1195,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/email-marketing-statistics-google-email-is-dead.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1200,3,'2015-12-03 11:45:09','2015-12-03 11:45:09','','email-marketing-statistics','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-statistics','','','2015-12-03 11:45:21','2015-12-03 11:45:21','',1195,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/email-marketing-statistics.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1201,3,'2015-12-03 11:53:05','2015-12-03 11:53:05','','email-marketing-statistics-reach','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-statistics-reach','','','2015-12-03 11:53:41','2015-12-03 11:53:41','',1195,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/email-marketing-statistics-reach.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1202,3,'2015-12-03 12:05:51','2015-12-03 12:05:51','','email-marketing-statistics-opening-environments','','inherit','open','closed','','email-marketing-statistics-opening-environments','','','2015-12-03 12:07:04','2015-12-03 12:07:04','',1195,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/email-marketing-statistics-opening-environments.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1205,3,'2015-12-08 10:56:29','2015-12-08 10:56:29','Email marketers spend a lot of time crafting email campaigns. From testing various email copy to crafting enticing subject lines in an attempt to maximize open rates and click through rates. But if your emails end up in peoples spam box instead of their inbox, your emails simply won\'t get read.\r\n\r\nA recent IBM study highlighted the impact deliverability rates can have on your email marketing. Their study found that 17% of emails never see the inside of the recipients inbox.\r\n\r\nThe only way to avoid spam filters is to understand how spam filters work and how you can avoid them. In this post we\'ll go through the effects bad deliverability can have on your campaigns, the different spam filters and how they work, and how to craft emails that will avoid spam filters.\r\n<h3>Effect of bad deliverability</h3>\r\nIn 2012 Sony launched an email marketing campaign to cross-sell the PlayStation Vita to existing PlayStation customers. The campaign was sent to 4.2 million people and resulted in 9,236 devices being sold, generating <a href=\"https://econsultancy.com/blog/65329-seven-inspirational-email-marketing-case-studies-from-the-digitals/\" target=\"_blank\">€2.9 million in revenue</a>.\r\n\r\nLets say for arguments sake that 17% of the emails sony sent out ended up in spam boxes. That\'s 714,000 emails. Had all those emails been delivered, sony could have potentially sold an extra 1919 units, generating an extra €602,537 in revenue. That being said, you\'re not going to have 100% deliverability. But there are tricks you can use to maximize your email deliverability rate.\r\n<h3>How spam filters work</h3>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">To maximize deliverability rates for your campaigns it is really important to have a basic knowledge of how spam filters actually work and on what basis they flag an email as spam.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Spam filters generally use a scoring framework and look at a few things when deciding what to do with emails: the sender\'s technical specifics, the email\'s content, reputation, and engagement.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><em>Technical Specifics</em></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Spam filters will typically check for appropriate email authentication and your sending IP\'s reputation when deciding whether to deliver your emails or make them disappear into cyberspace.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><em><strong>Content</strong></em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Here we\'re talking about the actual content that is in your subject line and body of the email. Spam filters work by scanning the entire copy of the email searching for specific words typically found in spammy emails. In addition to the copy of the email the filters will look at formatting, link types, and image-to-text ratio. Some services like gmail will also look at spammy text within an image using image recognition.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><em>User Defined</em></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">This is also know as bayesian filtering and it\'s one of the most widely used type of spam filters. These filters work by watching recipients classifying emails as junk. When a user classifies an email as spam the filter looks at the words and phrases in the subject line, email content, links, and so on. Over time, the filter learns to scan for those traits in every email.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Tactics for avoiding spam filters</h3>\r\nNow you know how spam filters work, her\'s how you can avoid them and maximize your email deliverability rate.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Avoid spam words</strong></em>\r\n\r\nOne of the fastest ways to end up in a subscriber\'s spam folder is to load your email up with words that most email service providers have identified as common words in spam email. A good rule of thumb is, if it sounds like salesman lingo then it\'s probably a spam trigger word.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately there isn\'t one simple list of a all the words you should avoid. This is because spam filters are so sophisticated and words will vary between industries.\r\n\r\nHere\'s some examples of spam words to avoid if you are in the financial or marketing space:\r\n\r\n<em>Financial</em>\r\n\r\n[su_table]\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>$$$</td>\r\n<td>Affordable</td>\r\n<td>Bargin</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cash</td>\r\n<td>Cash bonus</td>\r\n<td>Cheap</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>F r e e</td>\r\n<td>Fast cash</td>\r\n<td>For just $XXX</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Get out of debt</td>\r\n<td>No fees</td>\r\n<td>Save big money</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Save up to</td>\r\n<td>Stock alert</td>\r\n<td>Subject to credit</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Unsecured debt</td>\r\n<td>US dollars</td>\r\n<td>Why pay more</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n[/su_table]\r\n\r\n<em>Marketing</em>\r\n\r\n[su_table]\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Click here</td>\r\n<td>Email marketing</td>\r\n<td>Form</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Increase sales</td>\r\n<td>Increase traffic</td>\r\n<td>More internet traffic</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Internet marketing</td>\r\n<td>Marketing solutions</td>\r\n<td>Month trial offer</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Online marketing</td>\r\n<td>Visit our site</td>\r\n<td>Web traffic</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n[/su_table]\r\n\r\nFor a more comprehensive lists of words you should avoid, check out this industry specific <a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/30684/The-Ultimate-List-of-Email-SPAM-Trigger-Words.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">post by Hubspot</a>.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Formatting</strong></em>\r\n\r\nSuspicious formatting not only triggers spam filters, it might also annoy your recipients into marking your emails as a spam. Here are some basic formatting tips when designing your emails:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>AVOID CAPITAL LETTERS</strong> - avoid using capital letters in your email copy and subject lines.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Don\'t over-use punctuation marks!!!!!?</b> - try and avoid excessive use of punctuation marks, especially in a row.F</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Keep fonts consistent</strong> - avoid bright <span style=\"color: red;\">red</span> fonts or going crazy with <strong><span style=\"color: blue;\">c</span><span style=\"color: green;\">o</span><span style=\"color: yellow;\">l</span><span style=\"color: pink;\">o</span><span style=\"color: grey;\">r</span><span style=\"color: purple;\">s</span></strong>, styles, and formatting.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Provide an unsubscribe link</strong> - This is the law. If your emails are missing an unsubscribe link they\'ll trigger spam filters.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Don\'t link too much</strong> - try and include as few links as possible in your emails. For any links you do include, avoid using URL shorteners as they\'re frequently abused by spammers.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Make sure the HTML code is clean</strong> - sloppy HTML code can get you spam filtered. If you use a drag and drop editor to code your email sometimes they include useless code that\'s invisible to the user. This makes filters think you\'re a sloppy spammer.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Include text</strong> - Sometimes it can be appealing to just use a bunch of slick graphics and images. But spam filters can\'t read images so they assume you\'re a spammer trying to trick them.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Avoid mashing text with numbers</b> - creative spelling is a classic sign of a spammer trying to include words they shouldn\'t. For instance: Cl1ck h3r3 f0r fr33 cash.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<em><strong>Engagement</strong></em>\r\n\r\nSubscriber engagement is a huge part of getting emails into people\'s inboxes. If your subscribers consistently ignore your emails, failing to open and click your emails, mail servers are going to presume you\'re a spam sender. If your emails are getting low engagement they will end up in spam boxes, even if your subscribers aren\'t marking the email as spam.\r\n\r\nHere\'s some basic things you can do to avoid being flagged as spam if your emails have low engagement rates:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Have a policy for unengaged recipients</strong> - if someone is constantly ignoring your emails, remove them from your list. Keeping them on your list will do more harm than good.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Keep email frequency low</b> - if you\'re bombarding your subscribers with emails over a short period of time you\'re increasing the likelihood they will be unengaged.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Keep your email list current and clean</strong> - if you start sending campaigns to old lists and prospects then you\'re running the risk of the recipients marking your email as spam as they\'ve probably forgotten who you are.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Remove bounces</strong> - if an email bounces, remove that recipient from your list.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Takeaways</h3>\r\nEmail marketing continues to be one of the most effective channels. But if your emails aren\'t ending up in people\'s inboxes then your emails aren\'t going to get read and you\'ll miss out on all that potential revenue.\r\n\r\nNow you have a basic understanding of how spam filters work and how you can avoid them you should keep these tips in mind when crafting your next campaign.\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 25px;\" align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://birdleaf.io/free-customer-persona-guide\"><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/customer_persona_banner.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"center\" /></a></div>','How to avoid spam filters and increase email deliverability','','publish','open','open','','5-simple-ways-to-avoid-spam-filters-and-increase-email-deliverabiltiy','','','2015-12-08 10:58:11','2015-12-08 10:58:11','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?p=1205',0,'post','',0),(1206,3,'2015-12-08 10:53:18','2015-12-08 10:53:18','','How-to-avoid-spam-filters-cover','','inherit','open','closed','','how-to-avoid-spam-filters-cover','','','2015-12-08 10:53:18','2015-12-08 10:53:18','',1205,'http://birdleaf.io/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/How-to-avoid-spam-filters-cover.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1218,4,'2016-02-08 13:12:19','2016-02-08 13:12:19','It was great working with you! To pay your invoice just click the button below, enter your card details, and you\'ll receive a confirmation if your payment is successful.\r\n\r\n[stripe name=\"Birdleaf\" description=\"Birdleaf Email Processing\" amount=\"29402\"]','One Time Payment','','publish','closed','closed','','one-time-payment','','','2016-02-08 13:26:41','2016-02-08 13:26:41','',0,'http://birdleaf.io/?page_id=1218',0,'page','',0);
